126// If I is a shifted mask, set the size (Size) and the first bit of the
127// mask (Pos), and return true.
128// For example, if I is 0x003ff800, (Pos, Size) = (11, 11).
129static bool isShiftedMask(uint64_t I, uint64_t &Pos, uint64_t &Size) {
130 if (!isShiftedMask_64(I))
131 return false;
132
133 Size = countPopulation(I);
134 Pos = countTrailingZeros(I);
135 return true;
136}

138// The MIPS MSA ABI passes vector arguments in the integer register set.
139// The number of integer registers used is dependant on the ABI used.
140MVT MipsTargetLowering::getRegisterTypeForCallingConv(LLVMContext &Context,
141 CallingConv::ID CC,
142 EVT VT) const {
143 if (VT.isVector()) {
144 if (Subtarget.isABI_O32()) {
145 return MVT::i32;
146 } else {
147 return (VT.getSizeInBits() == 32) ? MVT::i32 : MVT::i64;
148 }
149 }
150 return MipsTargetLowering::getRegisterType(Context, VT);
151}
152
153unsigned MipsTargetLowering::getNumRegistersForCallingConv(LLVMContext &Context,
154 CallingConv::ID CC,
155 EVT VT) const {
156 if (VT.isVector())
157 return std::max((VT.getSizeInBits() / (Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? 32 : 64)),
158 1U);
159 return MipsTargetLowering::getNumRegisters(Context, VT);
160}
161
162unsigned MipsTargetLowering::getVectorTypeBreakdownForCallingConv(
163 LLVMContext &Context, CallingConv::ID CC, EVT VT, EVT &IntermediateVT,
164 unsigned &NumIntermediates, MVT &RegisterVT) const {
165 // Break down vector types to either 2 i64s or 4 i32s.
166 RegisterVT = getRegisterTypeForCallingConv(Context, CC, VT);
167 IntermediateVT = RegisterVT;
168 NumIntermediates = VT.getSizeInBits() < RegisterVT.getSizeInBits()
169 ? VT.getVectorNumElements()
170 : VT.getSizeInBits() / RegisterVT.getSizeInBits();
171
172 return NumIntermediates;
173}

175SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getGlobalReg(SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT Ty,
176 bool IsForTls) const {
177 MipsFunctionInfo *FI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
178 return DAG.getRegister(FI->getGlobalBaseReg(IsForTls), Ty);
179}
180
181SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getCapGlobalReg(SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT Ty) const {
182 assert(Ty.isFatPointer());
183 assert(ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
184 MipsFunctionInfo *FI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
185 return DAG.getRegister(FI->getCapGlobalBaseRegForGlobalISel(), Ty);
186}

188SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getTargetNode(GlobalAddressSDNode *N, EVT Ty,
189 SelectionDAG &DAG,
190 unsigned Flag) const {
191 return DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(N->getGlobal(), SDLoc(N), Ty, 0, Flag);
192}
193
194SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getTargetNode(ExternalSymbolSDNode *N, EVT Ty,
195 SelectionDAG &DAG,
196 unsigned Flag) const {
197 return DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(N->getSymbol(), Ty, Flag);
198}
199
200SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getTargetNode(BlockAddressSDNode *N, EVT Ty,
201 SelectionDAG &DAG,
202 unsigned Flag) const {
203 return DAG.getTargetBlockAddress(N->getBlockAddress(), Ty, 0, Flag);
204}
205
206SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getTargetNode(JumpTableSDNode *N, EVT Ty,
207 SelectionDAG &DAG,
208 unsigned Flag) const {
209 return DAG.getTargetJumpTable(N->getIndex(), Ty, Flag);
210}
211
212SDValue MipsTargetLowering::getTargetNode(ConstantPoolSDNode *N, EVT Ty,
213 SelectionDAG &DAG,
214 unsigned Flag) const {
215 return DAG.getTargetConstantPool(N->getConstVal(), Ty, N->getAlignment(),
216 N->getOffset(), Flag);
217}

350MipsTargetLowering::MipsTargetLowering(const MipsTargetMachine &TM,
351 const MipsSubtarget &STI)
352 : TargetLowering(TM), Subtarget(STI), ABI(TM.getABI()) {
353 CapType = STI.typeForCapabilities();
354 assert(cheriCapabilityType().isFatPointer());
355
356 // Mips does not have i1 type, so use i32 for
357 // setcc operations results (slt, sgt, ...).
358 setBooleanContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
359 setBooleanVectorContents(ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent);
360 // The cmp.cond.fmt instruction in MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6 uses 0 and -1 like MSA
361 // does. Integer booleans still use 0 and 1.
362 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6())
363 setBooleanContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent,
364 ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent);
365
366 // Load extented operations for i1 types must be promoted
367 for (MVT VT : MVT::integer_valuetypes()) {
368 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
369 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
370 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
371 }
372
373 // MIPS doesn't have extending float->double load/store. Set LoadExtAction
374 // for f32, f16
375 for (MVT VT : MVT::fp_valuetypes()) {
376 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::f32, Expand);
377 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::f16, Expand);
378 }
379
380 // Set LoadExtAction for f16 vectors to Expand
381 for (MVT VT : MVT::fp_vector_valuetypes()) {
382 MVT F16VT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f16, VT.getVectorNumElements());
383 if (F16VT.isValid())
384 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, F16VT, Expand);
385 }
386
387 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f32, MVT::f16, Expand);
388 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f64, MVT::f16, Expand);
389
390 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f64, MVT::f32, Expand);
391
392 // Used by legalize types to correctly generate the setcc result.
393 // Without this, every float setcc comes with a AND/OR with the result,
394 // we don't want this, since the fpcmp result goes to a flag register,
395 // which is used implicitly by brcond and select operations.
396 AddPromotedToType(ISD::SETCC, MVT::i1, MVT::i32);
397
398 // Trap is an invalid instruction sequence
399 setOperationAction(ISD::TRAP, MVT::Other, Legal);
400 if (Subtarget.isCheri()) {
401 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDRSPACECAST, CapType, Custom);
402 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDRSPACECAST, MVT::i64, Custom);
403 setOperationAction(ISD::ConstantPool, CapType, Custom);
404 }
405
406 // Mips Custom Operations
407 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalAddress, CapType, Custom);
408 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTls())
409 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, CapType, Custom);
410 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable())
411 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_JT, MVT::Other, Custom);
412 else
413 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_JT, MVT::Other, Expand);
414 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
415 setOperationAction(ISD::BlockAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
416 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, MVT::i32, Custom);
417 setOperationAction(ISD::JumpTable, MVT::i32, Custom);
418 setOperationAction(ISD::ConstantPool, MVT::i32, Custom);
419 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f32, Custom);
420 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f64, Custom);
421 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i32, Custom);
422 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f32, Custom);
423 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f64, Custom);
424 setOperationAction(ISD::BRCOND, MVT::Other, Custom);
425 setOperationAction(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, MVT::f32, Custom);
426 setOperationAction(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, MVT::f64, Custom);
427 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, MVT::i32, Custom);
428
429 if (!(TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath || Subtarget.inAbs2008Mode())) {
430 setOperationAction(ISD::FABS, MVT::f32, Custom);
431 setOperationAction(ISD::FABS, MVT::f64, Custom);
432 }
433
434 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) {
435 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalAddress, MVT::i64, Custom);
436 setOperationAction(ISD::BlockAddress, MVT::i64, Custom);
437 // Handle blockaddress in AS200:
438 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
439 setOperationAction(ISD::BlockAddress, CapType, Custom);
440
441 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, MVT::i64, Custom);
442 setOperationAction(ISD::JumpTable, MVT::i64, Custom);
443 setOperationAction(ISD::ConstantPool, MVT::i64, Custom);
444 //setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i64, Custom);
445 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::i64, Custom);
446 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, MVT::i64, Custom);
447 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, MVT::i64, Custom);
448 setOperationAction(ISD::SHL_PARTS, MVT::i64, Custom);
449 setOperationAction(ISD::SRA_PARTS, MVT::i64, Custom);
450 setOperationAction(ISD::SRL_PARTS, MVT::i64, Custom);
451 }
452
453 if (!Subtarget.isGP64bit()) {
454 setOperationAction(ISD::SHL_PARTS, MVT::i32, Custom);
455 setOperationAction(ISD::SRA_PARTS, MVT::i32, Custom);
456 setOperationAction(ISD::SRL_PARTS, MVT::i32, Custom);
457 }
458
459 setOperationAction(ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA, MVT::i32, Custom);
460 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit())

527 setOperationAction(ISD::FP16_TO_FP, MVT::f64, Expand);

599

612 if (Subtarget.isCheri())
613 MaxStoresPerMemcpy = MaxStoresPerMemmove = 15;
614
615 isMicroMips = Subtarget.inMicroMipsMode();
616}

619 const MipsSubtarget &STI) {

626// Create a fast isel object.
627FastISel *
628MipsTargetLowering::createFastISel(FunctionLoweringInfo &funcInfo,
629 const TargetLibraryInfo *libInfo) const {
630 const MipsTargetMachine &TM =
631 static_cast<const MipsTargetMachine &>(funcInfo.MF->getTarget());
632
633 // We support only the standard encoding [MIPS32,MIPS32R5] ISAs.
634 bool UseFastISel = TM.Options.EnableFastISel && Subtarget.hasMips32() &&
635 !Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.inMips16Mode() &&
636 !Subtarget.inMicroMipsMode();
637
638 // Disable if either of the following is true:
639 // We do not generate PIC, the ABI is not O32, LargeGOT is being used.
640 if (!TM.isPositionIndependent() || !TM.getABI().IsO32() || LargeGOT)
641 UseFastISel = false;
642
643 return UseFastISel ? Mips::createFastISel(funcInfo, libInfo) : nullptr;
644}

653static SDValue performDivRemCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
654 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
655 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
656 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps())
657 return SDValue();
658
659 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
660 unsigned LO = (Ty == MVT::i32) ? Mips::LO0 : Mips::LO0_64;
661 unsigned HI = (Ty == MVT::i32) ? Mips::HI0 : Mips::HI0_64;
662 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SDIVREM ? MipsISD::DivRem16 :
663 MipsISD::DivRemU16;
664 SDLoc DL(N);
665
666 SDValue DivRem = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, MVT::Glue,
667 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1));
668 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode();
669 SDValue InGlue = DivRem;
670
671 // insert MFLO
672 if (N->hasAnyUseOfValue(0)) {
673 SDValue CopyFromLo = DAG.getCopyFromReg(InChain, DL, LO, Ty,
674 InGlue);
675 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), CopyFromLo);
676 InChain = CopyFromLo.getValue(1);
677 InGlue = CopyFromLo.getValue(2);
678 }
679
680 // insert MFHI
681 if (N->hasAnyUseOfValue(1)) {
682 SDValue CopyFromHi = DAG.getCopyFromReg(InChain, DL,
683 HI, Ty, InGlue);
684 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), CopyFromHi);
685 }
686
687 return SDValue();
688}
689
690static Mips::CondCode condCodeToFCC(ISD::CondCode CC) {
691 switch (CC) {
692 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown fp condition code!");
693 case ISD::SETEQ:
694 case ISD::SETOEQ: return Mips::FCOND_OEQ;
695 case ISD::SETUNE: return Mips::FCOND_UNE;
696 case ISD::SETLT:
697 case ISD::SETOLT: return Mips::FCOND_OLT;
698 case ISD::SETGT:
699 case ISD::SETOGT: return Mips::FCOND_OGT;
700 case ISD::SETLE:
701 case ISD::SETOLE: return Mips::FCOND_OLE;
702 case ISD::SETGE:
703 case ISD::SETOGE: return Mips::FCOND_OGE;
704 case ISD::SETULT: return Mips::FCOND_ULT;
705 case ISD::SETULE: return Mips::FCOND_ULE;
706 case ISD::SETUGT: return Mips::FCOND_UGT;
707 case ISD::SETUGE: return Mips::FCOND_UGE;
708 case ISD::SETUO: return Mips::FCOND_UN;
709 case ISD::SETO: return Mips::FCOND_OR;
710 case ISD::SETNE:
711 case ISD::SETONE: return Mips::FCOND_ONE;
712 case ISD::SETUEQ: return Mips::FCOND_UEQ;
713 }
714}
715
716/// This function returns true if the floating point conditional branches and
717/// conditional moves which use condition code CC should be inverted.
718static bool invertFPCondCodeUser(Mips::CondCode CC) {
719 if (CC >= Mips::FCOND_F && CC <= Mips::FCOND_NGT)
720 return false;
721
722 assert((CC >= Mips::FCOND_T && CC <= Mips::FCOND_GT) &&
723 "Illegal Condition Code");
724
725 return true;
726}
727
728// Creates and returns an FPCmp node from a setcc node.
729// Returns Op if setcc is not a floating point comparison.
730static SDValue createFPCmp(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDValue &Op) {
731 // must be a SETCC node
732 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC)
733 return Op;
734
735 SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
736
737 if (!LHS.getValueType().isFloatingPoint())
738 return Op;
739
740 SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
741 SDLoc DL(Op);
742
743 // Assume the 3rd operand is a CondCodeSDNode. Add code to check the type of
744 // node if necessary.
745 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
746
747 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FPCmp, DL, MVT::Glue, LHS, RHS,
748 DAG.getConstant(condCodeToFCC(CC), DL, MVT::i32));
749}
750
751// Creates and returns a CMovFPT/F node.
752static SDValue createCMovFP(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Cond, SDValue True,
753 SDValue False, const SDLoc &DL) {
754 ConstantSDNode *CC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Cond.getOperand(2));
755 bool invert = invertFPCondCodeUser((Mips::CondCode)CC->getSExtValue());
756 SDValue FCC0 = DAG.getRegister(Mips::FCC0, MVT::i32);
757
758 return DAG.getNode((invert ? MipsISD::CMovFP_F : MipsISD::CMovFP_T), DL,
759 True.getValueType(), True, FCC0, False, Cond);
760}
761
762static SDValue performSELECTCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
763 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
764 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
765 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps())
766 return SDValue();
767
768 SDValue SetCC = N->getOperand(0);
769
770 if ((SetCC.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC) ||
771 !SetCC.getOperand(0).getValueType().isInteger())
772 return SDValue();
773
774 SDValue False = N->getOperand(2);
775 EVT FalseTy = False.getValueType();
776
777 if (!FalseTy.isInteger())
778 return SDValue();
779
780 ConstantSDNode *FalseC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(False);
781
782 // If the RHS (False) is 0, we swap the order of the operands
783 // of ISD::SELECT (obviously also inverting the condition) so that we can
784 // take advantage of conditional moves using the $0 register.
785 // Example:
786 // return (a != 0) ? x : 0;
787 // load $reg, x
788 // movz $reg, $0, a
789 if (!FalseC)
790 return SDValue();
791
792 const SDLoc DL(N);
793
794 if (!FalseC->getZExtValue()) {
795 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(SetCC.getOperand(2))->get();
796 SDValue True = N->getOperand(1);
797 EVT TrueVT = True.getValueType();
798 assert(TrueVT.isInteger());
799
800 SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC.getOperand(0),
801 SetCC.getOperand(1), ISD::getSetCCInverse(CC, TrueVT));
802
803 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, FalseTy, SetCC, False, True);
804 }
805
806 // If both operands are integer constants there's a possibility that we
807 // can do some interesting optimizations.
808 SDValue True = N->getOperand(1);
809 ConstantSDNode *TrueC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(True);
810
811 if (!TrueC || !True.getValueType().isInteger())
812 return SDValue();
813
814 // We'll also ignore MVT::i64 operands as this optimizations proves
815 // to be ineffective because of the required sign extensions as the result
816 // of a SETCC operator is always MVT::i32 for non-vector types.
817 if (True.getValueType() == MVT::i64)
818 return SDValue();
819
820 int64_t Diff = TrueC->getSExtValue() - FalseC->getSExtValue();
821
822 // 1) (a < x) ? y : y-1
823 // slti $reg1, a, x
824 // addiu $reg2, $reg1, y-1
825 if (Diff == 1)
826 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC, False);
827
828 // 2) (a < x) ? y-1 : y
829 // slti $reg1, a, x
830 // xor $reg1, $reg1, 1
831 // addiu $reg2, $reg1, y-1
832 if (Diff == -1) {
833 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(SetCC.getOperand(2))->get();
834 assert(True.getValueType().isInteger());
835 SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC.getOperand(0),
836 SetCC.getOperand(1),
837 ISD::getSetCCInverse(CC, True.getValueType()));
838 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC, True);
839 }
840
841 // Could not optimize.
842 return SDValue();
843}
844
845static SDValue performCMovFPCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
846 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
847 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
848 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps())
849 return SDValue();
850
851 SDValue ValueIfTrue = N->getOperand(0), ValueIfFalse = N->getOperand(2);
852
853 ConstantSDNode *FalseC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(ValueIfFalse);
854 if (!FalseC || FalseC->getZExtValue())
855 return SDValue();
856
857 // Since RHS (False) is 0, we swap the order of the True/False operands
858 // (obviously also inverting the condition) so that we can
859 // take advantage of conditional moves using the $0 register.
860 // Example:
861 // return (a != 0) ? x : 0;
862 // load $reg, x
863 // movz $reg, $0, a
864 unsigned Opc = (N->getOpcode() == MipsISD::CMovFP_T) ? MipsISD::CMovFP_F :
865 MipsISD::CMovFP_T;
866
867 SDValue FCC = N->getOperand(1), Glue = N->getOperand(3);
868 return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), ValueIfFalse.getValueType(),
869 ValueIfFalse, FCC, ValueIfTrue, Glue);
870}
871
872static SDValue performANDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
873 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
874 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
875 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasExtractInsert())
876 return SDValue();
877
878 SDValue FirstOperand = N->getOperand(0);
879 unsigned FirstOperandOpc = FirstOperand.getOpcode();
880 SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1);
881 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0);
882 SDLoc DL(N);
883
884 uint64_t Pos = 0, SMPos, SMSize;
885 ConstantSDNode *CN;
886 SDValue NewOperand;
887 unsigned Opc;
888
889 // Op's second operand must be a shifted mask.
890 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Mask)) ||
891 !isShiftedMask(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos, SMSize))
892 return SDValue();
893
894 if (FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SRA || FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SRL) {
895 // Pattern match EXT.
896 // $dst = and ((sra or srl) $src , pos), (2**size - 1)
897 // => ext $dst, $src, pos, size
898
899 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate.
900 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(FirstOperand.getOperand(1))))
901 return SDValue();
902
903 Pos = CN->getZExtValue();
904
905 // Return if the shifted mask does not start at bit 0 or the sum of its size
906 // and Pos exceeds the word's size.
907 if (SMPos != 0 || Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits())
908 return SDValue();
909
910 Opc = MipsISD::Ext;
911 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0);
912 } else if (FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SHL && Subtarget.hasCnMips()) {
913 // Pattern match CINS.
914 // $dst = and (shl $src , pos), mask
915 // => cins $dst, $src, pos, size
916 // mask is a shifted mask with consecutive 1's, pos = shift amount,
917 // size = population count.
918
919 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate.
920 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(FirstOperand.getOperand(1))))
921 return SDValue();
922
923 Pos = CN->getZExtValue();
924
925 if (SMPos != Pos || Pos >= ValTy.getSizeInBits() || SMSize >= 32 ||
926 Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits())
927 return SDValue();
928
929 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0);
930 // SMSize is 'location' (position) in this case, not size.
931 SMSize--;
932 Opc = MipsISD::CIns;
933 } else {
934 // Pattern match EXT.
935 // $dst = and $src, (2**size - 1) , if size > 16
936 // => ext $dst, $src, pos, size , pos = 0
937
938 // If the mask is <= 0xffff, andi can be used instead.
939 if (CN->getZExtValue() <= 0xffff)
940 return SDValue();
941
942 // Return if the mask doesn't start at position 0.
943 if (SMPos)
944 return SDValue();
945
946 Opc = MipsISD::Ext;
947 NewOperand = FirstOperand;
948 }
949 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ValTy, NewOperand,
950 DAG.getConstant(Pos, DL, MVT::i32),
951 DAG.getConstant(SMSize, DL, MVT::i32));
952}
953
954static SDValue performORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
955 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
956 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
957 // Pattern match INS.
958 // $dst = or (and $src1 , mask0), (and (shl $src, pos), mask1),
959 // where mask1 = (2**size - 1) << pos, mask0 = ~mask1
960 // => ins $dst, $src, size, pos, $src1
961 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasExtractInsert())
962 return SDValue();
963
964 SDValue And0 = N->getOperand(0), And1 = N->getOperand(1);
965 uint64_t SMPos0, SMSize0, SMPos1, SMSize1;
966 ConstantSDNode *CN, *CN1;
967
968 // See if Op's first operand matches (and $src1 , mask0).
969 if (And0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND)
970 return SDValue();
971
972 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(And0.getOperand(1))) ||
973 !isShiftedMask(~CN->getSExtValue(), SMPos0, SMSize0))
974 return SDValue();
975
976 // See if Op's second operand matches (and (shl $src, pos), mask1).
977 if (And1.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
978 And1.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
979
980 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(And1.getOperand(1))) ||
981 !isShiftedMask(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos1, SMSize1))
982 return SDValue();
983
984 // The shift masks must have the same position and size.
985 if (SMPos0 != SMPos1 || SMSize0 != SMSize1)
986 return SDValue();
987
988 SDValue Shl = And1.getOperand(0);
989
990 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Shl.getOperand(1))))
991 return SDValue();
992
993 unsigned Shamt = CN->getZExtValue();
994
995 // Return if the shift amount and the first bit position of mask are not the
996 // same.
997 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0);
998 if ((Shamt != SMPos0) || (SMPos0 + SMSize0 > ValTy.getSizeInBits()))
999 return SDValue();
1000
1001 SDLoc DL(N);
1002 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, ValTy, Shl.getOperand(0),
1003 DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32),
1004 DAG.getConstant(SMSize0, DL, MVT::i32),
1005 And0.getOperand(0));
1006 } else {
1007 // Pattern match DINS.
1008 // $dst = or (and $src, mask0), mask1
1009 // where mask0 = ((1 << SMSize0) -1) << SMPos0
1010 // => dins $dst, $src, pos, size
1011 if (~CN->getSExtValue() == ((((int64_t)1 << SMSize0) - 1) << SMPos0) &&
1012 ((SMSize0 + SMPos0 <= 64 && Subtarget.hasMips64r2()) ||
1013 (SMSize0 + SMPos0 <= 32))) {
1014 // Check if AND instruction has constant as argument
1015 bool isConstCase = And1.getOpcode() != ISD::AND;
1016 if (And1.getOpcode() == ISD::AND) {
1017 if (!(CN1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(And1->getOperand(1))))
1018 return SDValue();
1019 } else {
1020 if (!(CN1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))))
1021 return SDValue();
1022 }
1023 // Don't generate INS if constant OR operand doesn't fit into bits
1024 // cleared by constant AND operand.
1025 if (CN->getSExtValue() & CN1->getSExtValue())
1026 return SDValue();
1027
1028 SDLoc DL(N);
1029 EVT ValTy = N->getOperand(0)->getValueType(0);
1030 SDValue Const1;
1031 SDValue SrlX;
1032 if (!isConstCase) {
1033 Const1 = DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32);
1034 SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, And1->getValueType(0), And1, Const1);
1035 }
1036 return DAG.getNode(
1037 MipsISD::Ins, DL, N->getValueType(0),
1038 isConstCase
1039 ? DAG.getConstant(CN1->getSExtValue() >> SMPos0, DL, ValTy)
1040 : SrlX,
1041 DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32),
1042 DAG.getConstant(ValTy.getSizeInBits() / 8 < 8 ? SMSize0 & 31
1043 : SMSize0,
1044 DL, MVT::i32),
1045 And0->getOperand(0));
1046
1047 }
1048 return SDValue();
1049 }
1050}
1051
1052static SDValue performMADD_MSUBCombine(SDNode *ROOTNode, SelectionDAG &CurDAG,
1053 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1054 // ROOTNode must have a multiplication as an operand for the match to be
1055 // successful.
1056 if (ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::MUL &&
1057 ROOTNode->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::MUL)
1058 return SDValue();
1059
1060 // We don't handle vector types here.
1061 if (ROOTNode->getValueType(0).isVector())
1062 return SDValue();
1063
1064 // For MIPS64, madd / msub instructions are inefficent to use with 64 bit
1065 // arithmetic. E.g.
1066 // (add (mul a b) c) =>
1067 // let res = (madd (mthi (drotr c 32))x(mtlo c) a b) in
1068 // MIPS64: (or (dsll (mfhi res) 32) (dsrl (dsll (mflo res) 32) 32)
1069 // or
1070 // MIPS64R2: (dins (mflo res) (mfhi res) 32 32)
1071 //
1072 // The overhead of setting up the Hi/Lo registers and reassembling the
1073 // result makes this a dubious optimzation for MIPS64. The core of the
1074 // problem is that Hi/Lo contain the upper and lower 32 bits of the
1075 // operand and result.
1076 //
1077 // It requires a chain of 4 add/mul for MIPS64R2 to get better code
1078 // density than doing it naively, 5 for MIPS64. Additionally, using
1079 // madd/msub on MIPS64 requires the operands actually be 32 bit sign
1080 // extended operands, not true 64 bit values.
1081 //
1082 // FIXME: For the moment, disable this completely for MIPS64.
1083 if (Subtarget.hasMips64())
1084 return SDValue();
1085
1086 SDValue Mult = ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::MUL
1087 ? ROOTNode->getOperand(0)
1088 : ROOTNode->getOperand(1);
1089
1090 SDValue AddOperand = ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::MUL
1091 ? ROOTNode->getOperand(1)
1092 : ROOTNode->getOperand(0);
1093
1094 // Transform this to a MADD only if the user of this node is the add.
1095 // If there are other users of the mul, this function returns here.
1096 if (!Mult.hasOneUse())
1097 return SDValue();
1098
1099 // maddu and madd are unusual instructions in that on MIPS64 bits 63..31
1100 // must be in canonical form, i.e. sign extended. For MIPS32, the operands
1101 // of the multiply must have 32 or more sign bits, otherwise we cannot
1102 // perform this optimization. We have to check this here as we're performing
1103 // this optimization pre-legalization.
1104 SDValue MultLHS = Mult->getOperand(0);
1105 SDValue MultRHS = Mult->getOperand(1);
1106
1107 bool IsSigned = MultLHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND &&
1108 MultRHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
1109 bool IsUnsigned = MultLHS->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND &&
1110 MultRHS->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
1111
1112 if (!IsSigned && !IsUnsigned)
1113 return SDValue();
1114
1115 // Initialize accumulator.
1116 SDLoc DL(ROOTNode);
1117 SDValue TopHalf;
1118 SDValue BottomHalf;
1119 BottomHalf = CurDAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, AddOperand,
1120 CurDAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
1121
1122 TopHalf = CurDAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, AddOperand,
1123 CurDAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, DL));
1124 SDValue ACCIn = CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTLOHI, DL, MVT::Untyped,
1125 BottomHalf,
1126 TopHalf);
1127
1128 // Create MipsMAdd(u) / MipsMSub(u) node.
1129 bool IsAdd = ROOTNode->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD;
1130 unsigned Opcode = IsAdd ? (IsUnsigned ? MipsISD::MAddu : MipsISD::MAdd)
1131 : (IsUnsigned ? MipsISD::MSubu : MipsISD::MSub);
1132 SDValue MAddOps[3] = {
1133 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Mult->getOperand(0)),
1134 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Mult->getOperand(1)), ACCIn};
1135 EVT VTs[2] = {MVT::i32, MVT::i32};
1136 SDValue MAdd = CurDAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, MAddOps);
1137
1138 SDValue ResLo = CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, MVT::i32, MAdd);
1139 SDValue ResHi = CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, MVT::i32, MAdd);
1140 SDValue Combined =
1141 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, ResLo, ResHi);
1142 return Combined;
1143}
1144
1145static SDValue performSUBCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1146 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
1147 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1148 // (sub v0 (mul v1, v2)) => (msub v1, v2, v0)
1149 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) {
1150 if (Subtarget.hasMips32() && !Subtarget.hasMips32r6() &&
1151 !Subtarget.inMips16Mode() && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64)
1152 return performMADD_MSUBCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
1153
1154 return SDValue();
1155 }
1156
1157 return SDValue();
1158}
1159
1160static SDValue performADDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1161 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
1162 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1163 // (add v0 (mul v1, v2)) => (madd v1, v2, v0)
1164 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) {
1165 if (Subtarget.hasMips32() && !Subtarget.hasMips32r6() &&
1166 !Subtarget.inMips16Mode() && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64)
1167 return performMADD_MSUBCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
1168
1169 return SDValue();
1170 }
1171
1172 // (add v0, (add v1, abs_lo(tjt))) => (add (add v0, v1), abs_lo(tjt))
1173 SDValue Add = N->getOperand(1);
1174
1175 if (Add.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
1176 return SDValue();
1177
1178 SDValue Lo = Add.getOperand(1);
1179
1180 if ((Lo.getOpcode() != MipsISD::Lo) ||
1181 (Lo.getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::TargetJumpTable))
1182 return SDValue();
1183
1184 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0);
1185 SDLoc DL(N);
1186
1187 SDValue Add1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, ValTy, N->getOperand(0),
1188 Add.getOperand(0));
1189 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, ValTy, Add1, Lo);
1190}
1191
1192static SDValue performSHLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1193 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
1194 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1195 // Pattern match CINS.
1196 // $dst = shl (and $src , imm), pos
1197 // => cins $dst, $src, pos, size
1198
1199 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasCnMips())
1200 return SDValue();
1201
1202 SDValue FirstOperand = N->getOperand(0);
1203 unsigned FirstOperandOpc = FirstOperand.getOpcode();
1204 SDValue SecondOperand = N->getOperand(1);
1205 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0);
1206 SDLoc DL(N);
1207
1208 uint64_t Pos = 0, SMPos, SMSize;
1209 ConstantSDNode *CN;
1210 SDValue NewOperand;
1211
1212 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate.
1213 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(SecondOperand)))
1214 return SDValue();
1215
1216 Pos = CN->getZExtValue();
1217
1218 if (Pos >= ValTy.getSizeInBits())
1219 return SDValue();
1220
1221 if (FirstOperandOpc != ISD::AND)
1222 return SDValue();
1223
1224 // AND's second operand must be a shifted mask.
1225 if (!(CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(FirstOperand.getOperand(1))) ||
1226 !isShiftedMask(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos, SMSize))
1227 return SDValue();
1228
1229 // Return if the shifted mask does not start at bit 0 or the sum of its size
1230 // and Pos exceeds the word's size.
1231 if (SMPos != 0 || SMSize > 32 || Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits())
1232 return SDValue();
1233
1234 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0);
1235 // SMSize is 'location' (position) in this case, not size.
1236 SMSize--;
1237
1238 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CIns, DL, ValTy, NewOperand,
1239 DAG.getConstant(Pos, DL, MVT::i32),
1240 DAG.getConstant(SMSize, DL, MVT::i32));
1241}
1242
1243static inline bool isOptNone(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1244 return MF.getFunction().hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptimizeNone) ||
1245 MF.getTarget().getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None;
1246}
1247
1248static SDValue
1249performCIncOffsetToCandAddrCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1250 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
1251 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1252 // Don't do this combine for optnone functions
1253 if (isOptNone(DAG.getMachineFunction()))
1254 return SDValue();
1255
1256 // We could do this in tablegen too, but doing it here might enable
1257 // reuse of constants instead of always emitting the DNEGU. It also means
1258 // we don't have to duplicate the pattern for ptraddr and the incoffset intrinsic
1259 // Tablegen pattern:
1260 // def : Pat<(ptradd CheriOpnd: $r1, (sub (i64 0), (and (int_cheri_cap_address_get CheriOpnd: $r1), GPR64Opnd: $mask))),
1261 // (CAndAddr $r1, (DSUBu ZERO_64, GPR64Opnd:$mask))>;
1262
1263 // Could be ptraddr or incoffset
1264 SDValue FirstOperand;
1265 SDValue SecondOperand;
1266 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN) {
1267 FirstOperand = N->getOperand(1);
1268 SecondOperand = N->getOperand(2);
1269 } else {
1270 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::PTRADD);
1271 FirstOperand = N->getOperand(0);
1272 SecondOperand = N->getOperand(1);
1273 }
1274
1275 // Old pattern for __builtin_align() and C code that does the same thing (and
1276 // is also generated by cap_covers_pages() in CheriBSD a -O2)
1277 // t6: i64 = llvm.cheri.cap.address.get TargetConstant:i64<9>, t4
1278 // t8: i64 = and t6, Constant:i64<16383>
1279 // t10: i64 = sub nsw Constant:i64<0>, t8
1280 // t11: iFATPTR128 = PTRADD t4, t10
1281 // This can be folded to a CAndAddr with the negated mask (i.e. DSUBu ZERO,
1282 // mask).
1283
1284 if (SecondOperand->getOpcode() != ISD::SUB)
1285 return SDValue();
1286 if (auto SubConst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(SecondOperand->getOperand(0))) {
1287 if (!SubConst->isNullValue())
1288 return SDValue();
1289 } else {
1290 return SDValue();
1291 }
1292 // Second operand is a negate
1293 SDValue NegatedValue = SecondOperand->getOperand(1);
1294 if (NegatedValue->getOpcode() != ISD::AND)
1295 return SDValue();
1296
1297 SDValue AndSrc = NegatedValue->getOperand(0);
1298 SDValue Mask = NegatedValue->getOperand(1);
1299
1300 if (AndSrc->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN)
1301 return SDValue(); // Not a getaddr node
1302 unsigned IID = cast<ConstantSDNode>(AndSrc->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
1303 if (IID == Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get) {
1304 auto SrcCap = AndSrc->getOperand(1);
1305 if (SrcCap == FirstOperand) {
1306 // Same operand -> for getaddr and ptraddr -> can combine
1307 // (ptradd CheriOpnd: $r1, (sub (i64 0), (and (int_cheri_cap_address_get CheriOpnd: $r1), GPR64Opnd: $mask)
1308 SDLoc DL(N);
1309 EVT IndexVT = Mask->getValueType(0);
1310 auto NegatedMask = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, IndexVT, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, IndexVT), Mask);
1311 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapAndAddr, DL, FirstOperand->getValueType(0), SrcCap, NegatedMask);
1312 }
1313 }
1314
1315 // TODO: for __builtin_align_up() we could do a cincoffset and then candaddr
1316 // (or will that cause representability issues for values close to the end?)
1317 return SDValue();
1318}
1319
1320static SDValue performINTRINSIC_WO_CHAINCombine(
1321 SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
1322 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1323 SDLoc DL(N);
1324 unsigned IID = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
1325 EVT VT = Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
1326
1327 // Lower to our custom node, but with a truncate back to i1 so we can
1328 // replace its uses.
1329 switch (IID) {
1330 case Intrinsic::cheri_cap_tag_get: {
1331 SDValue IntRes = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapTagGet, DL, VT,
1332 N->getOperand(1));
1333 IntRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VT, IntRes,
1334 DAG.getValueType(MVT::i1));
1335 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, MVT::i1, IntRes,
1336 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ISD::SETNE);
1337 }
1338 case Intrinsic::cheri_cap_sealed_get: {
1339 SDValue IntRes = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapSealedGet, DL, VT,
1340 N->getOperand(1));
1341 IntRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VT, IntRes,
1342 DAG.getValueType(MVT::i1));
1343 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, MVT::i1, IntRes,
1344 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ISD::SETNE);
1345 }
1346 case Intrinsic::cheri_cap_subset_test: {
1347 SDValue IntRes = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapSubsetTest, DL, VT,
1348 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2));
1349 IntRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VT, IntRes,
1350 DAG.getValueType(MVT::i1));
1351 return DAG.getSetCC(DL, MVT::i1, IntRes,
1352 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ISD::SETNE);
1353 }
1354 case Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_increment: {
1355 return performCIncOffsetToCandAddrCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1356 }
1357 }
1358
1359 return SDValue();
1360}
1361
1362SDValue MipsTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI)
1363 const {
1364 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
1365 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
1366
1367 switch (Opc) {
1368 default: break;
1369 case ISD::SDIVREM:
1370 case ISD::UDIVREM:
1371 return performDivRemCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1372 case ISD::SELECT:
1373 return performSELECTCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1374 case MipsISD::CMovFP_F:
1375 case MipsISD::CMovFP_T:
1376 return performCMovFPCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1377 case ISD::AND:
1378 return performANDCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1379 case ISD::OR:
1380 return performORCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1381 case ISD::ADD:
1382 return performADDCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1383 case ISD::SHL:
1384 return performSHLCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1385 case ISD::SUB:
1386 return performSUBCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1387 case ISD::PTRADD:
1388 return performCIncOffsetToCandAddrCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1389 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
1390 return performINTRINSIC_WO_CHAINCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1391 }
1392
1393 return SDValue();
1394}

1418void
1419MipsTargetLowering::LowerOperationWrapper(SDNode *N,
1420 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
1421 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1422 SDValue Res = LowerOperation(SDValue(N, 0), DAG);
1423
1424 if (Res)
1425 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Res->getNumValues(); I != E; ++I)
1426 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(I));
1427}

1435
1436SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
1437LowerOperation(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const
1438{
1439 switch (Op.getOpcode())
1440 {
1441 case ISD::ADDRSPACECAST: return lowerADDRSPACECAST(Op, DAG);
1442 case ISD::BRCOND: return lowerBRCOND(Op, DAG);
1443 case ISD::ConstantPool: return lowerConstantPool(Op, DAG);
1444 case ISD::GlobalAddress: return lowerGlobalAddress(Op, DAG);
1445 case ISD::BlockAddress: return lowerBlockAddress(Op, DAG);
1446 case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress: return lowerGlobalTLSAddress(Op, DAG);
1447 case ISD::JumpTable: return lowerJumpTable(Op, DAG);
1448 case ISD::SELECT: return lowerSELECT(Op, DAG);
1449 case ISD::SETCC: return lowerSETCC(Op, DAG);
1450 case ISD::VASTART: return lowerVASTART(Op, DAG);
1451 case ISD::VAARG: return lowerVAARG(Op, DAG);
1452 case ISD::VACOPY: return lowerVACOPY(Op, DAG);
1453 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: return lowerFCOPYSIGN(Op, DAG);
1454 case ISD::FABS: return lowerFABS(Op, DAG);
1455 case ISD::FRAMEADDR: return lowerFRAMEADDR(Op, DAG);
1456 case ISD::RETURNADDR: return lowerRETURNADDR(Op, DAG);
1457 case ISD::EH_RETURN: return lowerEH_RETURN(Op, DAG);
1458 case ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE: return lowerATOMIC_FENCE(Op, DAG);
1459 case ISD::SHL_PARTS: return lowerShiftLeftParts(Op, DAG);
1460 case ISD::SRA_PARTS: return lowerShiftRightParts(Op, DAG, true);
1461 case ISD::SRL_PARTS: return lowerShiftRightParts(Op, DAG, false);
1462 case ISD::LOAD: return lowerLOAD(Op, DAG);
1463 case ISD::STORE: return lowerSTORE(Op, DAG);
1464 case ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA: return lowerEH_DWARF_CFA(Op, DAG);
1465 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: return lowerFP_TO_SINT(Op, DAG);
1466 case ISD::BR_JT: return lowerBR_JT(Op, DAG);
1467 }
1468 return SDValue();
1469}

1485
1486static MachineBasicBlock *insertDivByZeroTrap(MachineInstr &MI,
1487 MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
1488 const TargetInstrInfo &TII,
1489 bool Is64Bit, bool IsMicroMips) {
1490 if (NoZeroDivCheck)
1491 return &MBB;
1492
1493 // Insert instruction "teq $divisor_reg, $zero, 7".
1494 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI);
1495 MachineInstrBuilder MIB;
1496 MachineOperand &Divisor = MI.getOperand(2);
1497 MIB = BuildMI(MBB, std::next(I), MI.getDebugLoc(),
1498 TII.get(IsMicroMips ? Mips::TEQ_MM : Mips::TEQ))
1499 .addReg(Divisor.getReg(), getKillRegState(Divisor.isKill()))
1500 .addReg(Mips::ZERO)
1501 .addImm(7);
1502
1503 // Use the 32-bit sub-register if this is a 64-bit division.
1504 if (Is64Bit)
1505 MIB->getOperand(0).setSubReg(Mips::sub_32);
1506
1507 // Clear Divisor's kill flag.
1508 Divisor.setIsKill(false);
1509
1510 // We would normally delete the original instruction here but in this case
1511 // we only needed to inject an additional instruction rather than replace it.
1512
1513 return &MBB;
1514}
1515
1516MachineBasicBlock *
1517MipsTargetLowering::EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(MachineInstr &MI,
1518 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
1519 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1520 default:
1521 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instr type to insert");
1522 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8:
1523 return emitAtomicBinaryPartword(MI, BB, 1);
1524 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16:
1525 return emitAtomicBinaryPartword(MI, BB, 2);
1526 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32:
1527 return emitAtomicBinary(MI, BB);
1528 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64:
1529 return emitAtomicBinary(MI, BB);
1530 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8:
1531 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16:
1532 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32:
1533 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64:
1534 // TODO: Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_CAP:
1535 return emitAtomicBinary(MI, BB);
1536
1537 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I8:

1706static unsigned getCheriPostRAAtomicOp(const MachineInstr &MI,
1707 bool* IsCapabilityArg) {
1708#define CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(op) \
1709 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I8: return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I8_POSTRA; \
1710 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I16: return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I16_POSTRA; \
1711 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I32: return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I32_POSTRA; \
1712 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I64: return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_I64_POSTRA;
1713
1714 // TODO: case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_CAP: return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_##op##_CAP_POSTRA;
1715
1716 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1717 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_ADD)
1718 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_SUB)
1719 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_AND)
1720 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_OR)
1721 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_XOR)
1722 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(LOAD_NAND)
1723 CAP_ATOMIC_POSTRA_CASES(SWAP)
1724 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_SWAP_CAP:
1725 *IsCapabilityArg = true;
1726 return Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_SWAP_CAP_POSTRA;
1727 default:
1728 llvm_unreachable("Unknown pseudo atomic for replacement!");
1729 }
1730}

1732// This function also handles Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32 (when BinOpcode == 0), and
1733// Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32 (when Nand == true)
1734MachineBasicBlock *
1735MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicBinary(MachineInstr &MI,
1736 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
1737
1738 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent();
1739 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo();
1740 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
1741 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
1742
1743 unsigned AtomicOp;
1744 bool IsCapabilityArg = false;
1745 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1746 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32:
1747 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32_POSTRA;
1748 break;
1749 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I32:
1750 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I32_POSTRA;
1751 break;
1752 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I32:
1753 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I32_POSTRA;
1754 break;
1755 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I32:
1756 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I32_POSTRA;
1757 break;
1758 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I32:
1759 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I32_POSTRA;
1760 break;
1761 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32:
1762 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32_POSTRA;
1763 break;
1764 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32:
1765 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32_POSTRA;
1766 break;
1767 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64:
1768 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64_POSTRA;
1769 break;
1770 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I64:
1771 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I64_POSTRA;
1772 break;
1773 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I64:
1774 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I64_POSTRA;
1775 break;
1776 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I64:
1777 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I64_POSTRA;
1778 break;
1779 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I64:
1780 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I64_POSTRA;
1781 break;
1782 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I64:
1783 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I64_POSTRA;
1784 break;
1785 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I64:
1786 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I64_POSTRA;
1787 break;
1788 default:
1789 AtomicOp = getCheriPostRAAtomicOp(MI, &IsCapabilityArg);
1790 break;
1791 }
1792
1793 unsigned OldVal = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
1794 auto RC = RegInfo.getRegClass(OldVal);
1795 // For capability cscc we want a GPR64 scratch register and not CheriGPR
1796 if (IsCapabilityArg)
1797 RC = &Mips::GPR64RegClass;
1798 unsigned Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
1799 unsigned Incr = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
1800 unsigned Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1801
1802 MachineBasicBlock::iterator II(MI);
1803
1804 // The scratch registers here with the EarlyClobber | Define | Implicit
1805 // flags is used to persuade the register allocator and the machine
1806 // verifier to accept the usage of this register. This has to be a real
1807 // register which has an UNDEF value but is dead after the instruction which
1808 // is unique among the registers chosen for the instruction.
1809
1810 // The EarlyClobber flag has the semantic properties that the operand it is
1811 // attached to is clobbered before the rest of the inputs are read. Hence it
1812 // must be unique among the operands to the instruction.
1813 // The Define flag is needed to coerce the machine verifier that an Undef
1814 // value isn't a problem.
1815 // The Dead flag is needed as the value in scratch isn't used by any other
1816 // instruction. Kill isn't used as Dead is more precise.
1817 // The implicit flag is here due to the interaction between the other flags
1818 // and the machine verifier.
1819
1820 // For correctness purpose, a new pseudo is introduced here. We need this
1821 // new pseudo, so that FastRegisterAllocator does not see an ll/sc sequence
1822 // that is spread over >1 basic blocks. A register allocator which
1823 // introduces (or any codegen infact) a store, can violate the expectations
1824 // of the hardware.
1825 //
1826 // An atomic read-modify-write sequence starts with a linked load
1827 // instruction and ends with a store conditional instruction. The atomic
1828 // read-modify-write sequence fails if any of the following conditions
1829 // occur between the execution of ll and sc:
1830 // * A coherent store is completed by another process or coherent I/O
1831 // module into the block of synchronizable physical memory containing
1832 // the word. The size and alignment of the block is
1833 // implementation-dependent.
1834 // * A coherent store is executed between an LL and SC sequence on the
1835 // same processor to the block of synchornizable physical memory
1836 // containing the word.
1837 //
1838
1839 unsigned PtrCopy = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(Ptr));
1840 // If the increment is NULL/ZERO we might not have to make a copy since it
1841 // will be a constant physical register
1842 unsigned IncrCopy = Incr;
1843 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(Incr)) {
1844 IncrCopy = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(Incr));
1845 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), IncrCopy).addReg(Incr);
1846 } else {
1847 assert(RegInfo.isConstantPhysReg(Incr));
1848 }
1849 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), PtrCopy).addReg(Ptr);
1850
1851 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp))
1852 .addReg(OldVal, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber)
1853 .addReg(PtrCopy)
1854 .addReg(IncrCopy)
1855 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber |
1856 RegState::Implicit | RegState::Dead);
1857
1858 MI.eraseFromParent();
1859
1860 return BB;
1861}
1862
1863MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitSignExtendToI32InReg(
1864 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size, unsigned DstReg,
1865 unsigned SrcReg) const {
1866 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
1867 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
1868
1869 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2() && Size == 1) {
1870 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SEB), DstReg).addReg(SrcReg);
1871 return BB;
1872 }
1873
1874 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2() && Size == 2) {
1875 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SEH), DstReg).addReg(SrcReg);
1876 return BB;
1877 }
1878
1879 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent();
1880 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo();
1881 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32);
1882 unsigned ScrReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1883
1884 assert(Size < 32);
1885 int64_t ShiftImm = 32 - (Size * 8);
1886
1887 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ScrReg).addReg(SrcReg).addImm(ShiftImm);
1888 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SRA), DstReg).addReg(ScrReg).addImm(ShiftImm);
1889
1890 return BB;
1891}
1892
1893MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicBinaryPartword(
1894 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size) const {
1895 assert((Size == 1 || Size == 2) &&
1896 "Unsupported size for EmitAtomicBinaryPartial.");
1897 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent();
1898 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo();
1899 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32);
1900 const bool ArePtrs64bit = ABI.ArePtrs64bit();
1901 const TargetRegisterClass *RCp =
1902 getRegClassFor(ArePtrs64bit ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32);
1903 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
1904 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
1905
1906 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
1907 unsigned Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
1908 unsigned Incr = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
1909
1910 unsigned AlignedAddr = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp);
1911 unsigned ShiftAmt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1912 unsigned Mask = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1913 unsigned Mask2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1914 unsigned Incr2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1915 unsigned MaskLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp);
1916 unsigned PtrLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1917 unsigned MaskUpper = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1918 unsigned Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1919 unsigned Scratch2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1920 unsigned Scratch3 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
1921
1922 unsigned AtomicOp = 0;
1923 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1924 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I8:
1925 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I8_POSTRA;
1926 break;
1927 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I16:
1928 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I16_POSTRA;
1929 break;
1930 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I8:
1931 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I8_POSTRA;
1932 break;
1933 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I16:
1934 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I16_POSTRA;
1935 break;
1936 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8:
1937 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8_POSTRA;
1938 break;
1939 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16:
1940 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16_POSTRA;
1941 break;
1942 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I8:
1943 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I8_POSTRA;
1944 break;
1945 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I16:
1946 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I16_POSTRA;
1947 break;
1948 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I8:
1949 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I8_POSTRA;
1950 break;
1951 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I16:
1952 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I16_POSTRA;
1953 break;
1954 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I8:
1955 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I8_POSTRA;
1956 break;
1957 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I16:
1958 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I16_POSTRA;
1959 break;
1960 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I8:
1961 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I8_POSTRA;
1962 break;
1963 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I16:
1964 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I16_POSTRA;
1965 break;
1966 default:
1967 llvm_unreachable("Unknown subword atomic pseudo for expansion!");
1968 }
1969
1970 // insert new blocks after the current block
1971 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
1972 MachineBasicBlock *exitMBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
1973 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
1974 MF->insert(It, exitMBB);
1975
1976 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to exitMBB.
1977 exitMBB->splice(exitMBB->begin(), BB,
1978 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
1979 exitMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
1980
1981 BB->addSuccessor(exitMBB, BranchProbability::getOne());
1982
1983 // thisMBB:
1984 // addiu masklsb2,$0,-4 # 0xfffffffc
1985 // and alignedaddr,ptr,masklsb2
1986 // andi ptrlsb2,ptr,3
1987 // sll shiftamt,ptrlsb2,3
1988 // ori maskupper,$0,255 # 0xff
1989 // sll mask,maskupper,shiftamt
1990 // nor mask2,$0,mask
1991 // sll incr2,incr,shiftamt
1992
1993 int64_t MaskImm = (Size == 1) ? 255 : 65535;
1994 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ABI.GetPtrAddiuOp()), MaskLSB2)
1995 .addReg(ABI.GetNullPtr()).addImm(-4);
1996 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ABI.GetPtrAndOp()), AlignedAddr)
1997 .addReg(Ptr).addReg(MaskLSB2);
1998 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), PtrLSB2)
1999 .addReg(Ptr, 0, ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::sub_32 : 0).addImm(3);
2000 if (Subtarget.isLittle()) {
2001 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm(3);
2002 } else {
2003 unsigned Off = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2004 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::XORi), Off)
2005 .addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm((Size == 1) ? 3 : 2);
2006 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(Off).addImm(3);
2007 }
2008 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ORi), MaskUpper)
2009 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(MaskImm);
2010 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Mask)
2011 .addReg(MaskUpper).addReg(ShiftAmt);
2012 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::NOR), Mask2).addReg(Mips::ZERO).addReg(Mask);
2013 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Incr2).addReg(Incr).addReg(ShiftAmt);
2014
2015
2016 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers is explained in
2017 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to
2018 // be undef, that is unique among registers chosen for the instruction.
2019
2020 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp))
2021 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber)
2022 .addReg(AlignedAddr)
2023 .addReg(Incr2)
2024 .addReg(Mask)
2025 .addReg(Mask2)
2026 .addReg(ShiftAmt)
2027 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2028 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit)
2029 .addReg(Scratch2, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2030 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit)
2031 .addReg(Scratch3, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2032 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit);
2033
2034 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now.
2035
2036 return exitMBB;
2037}

2039// Lower atomic compare and swap to a pseudo instruction, taking care to
2040// define a scratch register for the pseudo instruction's expansion. The
2041// instruction is expanded after the register allocator as to prevent
2042// the insertion of stores between the linked load and the store conditional.
2043
2044MachineBasicBlock *
2045MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicCmpSwap(MachineInstr &MI,
2046 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
2047
2048 unsigned AtomicOp = -1;
2049 bool IsCheriOp = false;
2050 MVT ScratchTy;
2051 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2052 case Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32:
2053 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32_POSTRA;
2054 ScratchTy = MVT::i32;
2055 break;
2056 case Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64:
2057 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64_POSTRA;
2058 ScratchTy = MVT::i64;
2059 break;
2060 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8:
2061 IsCheriOp = true;
2062 AtomicOp = Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8_POSTRA;
2063 ScratchTy = MVT::i32;
2064 break;
2065 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I16:
2066 IsCheriOp = true;
2067 AtomicOp = Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I16_POSTRA;
2068 ScratchTy = MVT::i32;
2069 break;
2070 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32:
2071 IsCheriOp = true;
2072 AtomicOp = Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32_POSTRA;
2073 ScratchTy = MVT::i32;
2074 break;
2075 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64:
2076 IsCheriOp = true;
2077 AtomicOp = Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64_POSTRA;
2078 ScratchTy = MVT::i64;
2079 break;
2080 case Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_CAP:
2081 IsCheriOp = true;
2082 AtomicOp = Mips::CAP_ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_CAP_POSTRA;
2083 ScratchTy = MVT::i64;
2084 break;
2085 default:
2086 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported atomic pseudo for EmitAtomicCmpSwap.");
2087 }
2088
2089 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent();
2090 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo();
2091 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(ScratchTy);
2092 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
2093 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
2094
2095 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2096 unsigned Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2097 unsigned OldVal = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2098 unsigned NewVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
2099
2100 unsigned Scratch = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2101 MachineBasicBlock::iterator II(MI);
2102
2103 // We need to create copies of the various registers and kill them at the
2104 // atomic pseudo. If the copies are not made, when the atomic is expanded
2105 // after fast register allocation, the spills will end up outside of the
2106 // blocks that their values are defined in, causing livein errors.
2107
2108 unsigned PtrCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(Ptr));
2109
2110 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), PtrCopy).addReg(Ptr);
2111
2112 // If one of the operands is NULL it was replaced with $CNULL/ZERO so we don't
2113 // need to create a copy in that case.
2114 unsigned OldValCopy = OldVal;
2115 unsigned NewValCopy = NewVal;
2116 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(OldValCopy)) {
2117 OldValCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(OldVal));
2118 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), OldValCopy).addReg(OldVal);
2119 } else {
2120 assert(MRI.isConstantPhysReg(OldValCopy));
2121 }
2122 if (TargetRegisterInfo::isVirtualRegister(NewValCopy)) {
2123 NewValCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(NewVal));
2124 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), NewValCopy).addReg(NewVal);
2125 } else {
2126 assert(MRI.isConstantPhysReg(NewVal));
2127 }
2128
2129 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers is explained in
2130 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to
2131 // be undef, that is unique among registers chosen for the instruction.
2132
2133 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp))
2134 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber)
2135 .addReg(PtrCopy, RegState::Kill)
2136 .addReg(OldValCopy, RegState::Kill)
2137 .addReg(NewValCopy, RegState::Kill)
2138 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2139 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit);
2140
2141 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now.
2142
2143 return BB;
2144}
2145
2146MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicCmpSwapPartword(
2147 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size) const {
2148 assert((Size == 1 || Size == 2) &&
2149 "Unsupported size for EmitAtomicCmpSwapPartial.");
2150
2151 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent();
2152 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo();
2153 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32);
2154 const bool ArePtrs64bit = ABI.ArePtrs64bit();
2155 const TargetRegisterClass *RCp =
2156 getRegClassFor(ArePtrs64bit ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32);
2157 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
2158 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
2159
2160 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
2161 unsigned Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
2162 unsigned CmpVal = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
2163 unsigned NewVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
2164
2165 unsigned AlignedAddr = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp);
2166 unsigned ShiftAmt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2167 unsigned Mask = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2168 unsigned Mask2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2169 unsigned ShiftedCmpVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2170 unsigned ShiftedNewVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2171 unsigned MaskLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp);
2172 unsigned PtrLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2173 unsigned MaskUpper = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2174 unsigned MaskedCmpVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2175 unsigned MaskedNewVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2176 unsigned AtomicOp = MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8
2177 ? Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8_POSTRA
2178 : Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I16_POSTRA;
2179
2180 // The scratch registers here with the EarlyClobber | Define | Dead | Implicit
2181 // flags are used to coerce the register allocator and the machine verifier to
2182 // accept the usage of these registers.
2183 // The EarlyClobber flag has the semantic properties that the operand it is
2184 // attached to is clobbered before the rest of the inputs are read. Hence it
2185 // must be unique among the operands to the instruction.
2186 // The Define flag is needed to coerce the machine verifier that an Undef
2187 // value isn't a problem.
2188 // The Dead flag is needed as the value in scratch isn't used by any other
2189 // instruction. Kill isn't used as Dead is more precise.
2190 unsigned Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2191 unsigned Scratch2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2192
2193 // insert new blocks after the current block
2194 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
2195 MachineBasicBlock *exitMBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
2196 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
2197 MF->insert(It, exitMBB);
2198
2199 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to exitMBB.
2200 exitMBB->splice(exitMBB->begin(), BB,
2201 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
2202 exitMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
2203
2204 BB->addSuccessor(exitMBB, BranchProbability::getOne());
2205
2206 // thisMBB:
2207 // addiu masklsb2,$0,-4 # 0xfffffffc
2208 // and alignedaddr,ptr,masklsb2
2209 // andi ptrlsb2,ptr,3
2210 // xori ptrlsb2,ptrlsb2,3 # Only for BE
2211 // sll shiftamt,ptrlsb2,3
2212 // ori maskupper,$0,255 # 0xff
2213 // sll mask,maskupper,shiftamt
2214 // nor mask2,$0,mask
2215 // andi maskedcmpval,cmpval,255
2216 // sll shiftedcmpval,maskedcmpval,shiftamt
2217 // andi maskednewval,newval,255
2218 // sll shiftednewval,maskednewval,shiftamt
2219 int64_t MaskImm = (Size == 1) ? 255 : 65535;
2220 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::DADDiu : Mips::ADDiu), MaskLSB2)
2221 .addReg(ABI.GetNullPtr()).addImm(-4);
2222 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::AND64 : Mips::AND), AlignedAddr)
2223 .addReg(Ptr).addReg(MaskLSB2);
2224 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), PtrLSB2)
2225 .addReg(Ptr, 0, ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::sub_32 : 0).addImm(3);
2226 if (Subtarget.isLittle()) {
2227 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm(3);
2228 } else {
2229 unsigned Off = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
2230 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::XORi), Off)
2231 .addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm((Size == 1) ? 3 : 2);
2232 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(Off).addImm(3);
2233 }
2234 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ORi), MaskUpper)
2235 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(MaskImm);
2236 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Mask)
2237 .addReg(MaskUpper).addReg(ShiftAmt);
2238 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::NOR), Mask2).addReg(Mips::ZERO).addReg(Mask);
2239 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), MaskedCmpVal)
2240 .addReg(CmpVal).addImm(MaskImm);
2241 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), ShiftedCmpVal)
2242 .addReg(MaskedCmpVal).addReg(ShiftAmt);
2243 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), MaskedNewVal)
2244 .addReg(NewVal).addImm(MaskImm);
2245 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), ShiftedNewVal)
2246 .addReg(MaskedNewVal).addReg(ShiftAmt);
2247
2248 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers are explained in
2249 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to
2250 // be undef, that is unique among the register chosen for the instruction.
2251
2252 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp))
2253 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber)
2254 .addReg(AlignedAddr)
2255 .addReg(Mask)
2256 .addReg(ShiftedCmpVal)
2257 .addReg(Mask2)
2258 .addReg(ShiftedNewVal)
2259 .addReg(ShiftAmt)
2260 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2261 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit)
2262 .addReg(Scratch2, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define |
2263 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit);
2264
2265 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now.
2266
2267 return exitMBB;
2268}

2287static void addGlobalsCSetBoundsStats(const GlobalValue *GV, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2288 StringRef Pass, const DebugLoc &DL) {
2289 int64_t AllocSize = -1;
2290 Optional<uint64_t> Size = None;
2291 if (GV->getValueType()->isSized()) {
2292 Size = DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(GV->getValueType());
2293 AllocSize = DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(GV->getValueType());
2294 }
2295 cheri::CSetBoundsStats->add(
2296 GV->getAlignment(), Size, Pass, cheri::SetBoundsPointerSource::GlobalVar,
2297 "load of global " + GV->getName() + " (alloc size=" + Twine(AllocSize) +
2298 ")",
2299 cheri::inferSourceLocation(DL, DAG.getMachineFunction().getName()));
