2301
2302SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerADDRSPACECAST(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG)
2303 const {
2304 SDLoc DL(Op);
2305 SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
2306 EVT DstTy = Op.getValueType();
2307 // A noop addrspacecast can happen when using the cap table because functions
2308 // can not yet be in AS200
2309 if (Src.getValueType() == Op.getValueType())
2310 return Src;
2311 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable()) {
2312 // XXXAR: HACK for the capability table (we turn this into an iFATPTR later
2313 // so we can just return the value
2314 if (isa<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Src)) {
2315 return Op;
2316 }
2317 }
2318 if (Src.getValueType() == MVT::i64) {
2319 assert(Op.getValueType() == CapType);
2320 bool IsFunction = false;
2321 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GN = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Src)) {
2322 IsFunction = isa<Function>(GN->getGlobal()->getBaseObject());
2323 }
2324 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Lowering addrspacecast: "; Op.dump(&DAG));
2325 // INTTOPTR will lower to a cincoffset on null in the purecap ABI, so we
2326 // need to use cfromddc here to keep the legacy ABI working:
2327 SDValue Ptr = IsFunction ? setPccOffset(DAG, DL, Src) : cFromDDC(DAG, DL, Src);
2328 if (auto *N = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Src)) {
2329 const GlobalValue *GV = N->getGlobal();
2330 auto *Ty = GV->getValueType();
2331 if (Ty->isSized() && (GV->hasInternalLinkage() || GV->hasLocalLinkage())){
2332 uint64_t SizeBytes = DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Ty);
2333 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats) {
2334 addGlobalsCSetBoundsStats(GV, DAG, "MipsTargetLowering::lowerADDRSPACECAST",
2335 N->getDebugLoc());
2336 }
2337 Ptr = setBounds(DAG, Ptr, SizeBytes, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
2338 }
2339 }
2340 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Lowering addrspacecast result: "; Ptr.dump(&DAG));
2341 return Ptr;
2342 }
2343 assert(Src.getValueType() == CapType);
2344 assert(Op.getValueType() == MVT::i64);
2345 assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTable() && "Should not generate ptrtoint in captable");
2346 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRTOINT, DL, DstTy, Src);
2347}
2348
2349SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerBRCOND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2350 // The first operand is the chain, the second is the condition, the third is
2351 // the block to branch to if the condition is true.
2352 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
2353 SDValue Dest = Op.getOperand(2);
2354 SDLoc DL(Op);
2355
2356 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6());
2357 SDValue CondRes = createFPCmp(DAG, Op.getOperand(1));
2358
2359 // Return if flag is not set by a floating point comparison.
2360 if (CondRes.getOpcode() != MipsISD::FPCmp)
2361 return Op;
2362
2363 SDValue CCNode = CondRes.getOperand(2);
2364 Mips::CondCode CC =
2365 (Mips::CondCode)cast<ConstantSDNode>(CCNode)->getZExtValue();
2366 unsigned Opc = invertFPCondCodeUser(CC) ? Mips::BRANCH_F : Mips::BRANCH_T;
2367 SDValue BrCode = DAG.getConstant(Opc, DL, MVT::i32);
2368 SDValue FCC0 = DAG.getRegister(Mips::FCC0, MVT::i32);
2369 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FPBrcond, DL, Op.getValueType(), Chain, BrCode,
2370 FCC0, Dest, CondRes);
2371}
2372
2373SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
2374lowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const
2375{
2376 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6());
2377 SDValue Cond = createFPCmp(DAG, Op.getOperand(0));
2378
2379 // Return if flag is not set by a floating point comparison.
2380 if (Cond.getOpcode() != MipsISD::FPCmp)
2381 return Op;
2382
2383 return createCMovFP(DAG, Cond, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2),
2384 SDLoc(Op));
2385}
2386
2387SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerSETCC(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2388 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6());
2389 SDValue Cond = createFPCmp(DAG, Op);
2390
2391 assert(Cond.getOpcode() == MipsISD::FPCmp &&
2392 "Floating point operand expected.");
2393
2394 SDLoc DL(Op);
2395 SDValue True = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
2396 SDValue False = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
2397
2398 return createCMovFP(DAG, Cond, True, False, DL);
2399}
2400
2401SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerGlobalAddress(SDValue Op,
2402 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2403 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType();
2404 GlobalAddressSDNode *N = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
2405 const GlobalValue *GV = N->getGlobal();
2406 const Type *GVTy = GV->getType();
2407 if (Ty.isFatPointer() && cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats) {
2408 addGlobalsCSetBoundsStats(GV, DAG, "MipsTargetLowering::lowerGlobalAddress",
2409 N->getDebugLoc());
2410 }
2411
2412 if (Subtarget.getABI().IsCheriPureCap() && Subtarget.useCheriCapTable()) {
2413 // FIXME: shouldn't functions have a R_MIPS_CHERI_CAPCALL relocation?
2414 bool CanUseCapTable = GVTy->isFunctionTy() || DAG.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(GVTy);
2415 EVT GlobalTy = Ty.isFatPointer() ? Ty : CapType;
2416 bool IsFnPtr =
2417 GVTy->isPointerTy() && GVTy->getPointerElementType()->isFunctionTy();
2418
2419 if (IsFnPtr) {
2420 // FIXME: in the future it would be good to inline local function pointers
2421 // into the capability table directly (right now the value is a
2422 // void () addrspace(200)* addrspace(200)* instead of a
2423 // void () addrspace(200)*
2424 // llvm::errs() << "is fn ptr: " << IsFnPtr << "\n";
2425
2426 if (!CanUseCapTable) {
2427 // Functions didn't have address spaces yet which is why this hack was
2428 // needed. See https://reviews.llvm.org/D37054
2429 // Should no longer be the case now so lets report and error
2430 report_fatal_error("Found function " + GV->getName() +
2431 " not in AS200. Compiling old IR?");
2432 CanUseCapTable = true;
2433 }
2434 }
2435 if (!CanUseCapTable && !GV->isThreadLocal()) {
2436 if (GVTy->getPointerAddressSpace() == 0) {
2437 errs() << "warning: Found global in default address space: "
2438 << GV->getName()
2439 << ". This should not happen, assuming it is AS200 for now\n";
2440 CanUseCapTable = true;
2441 Ty = CapType; // Ensure that we load a capability and not an i64
2442 }
2443 }
2444 if (CanUseCapTable) {
2445 // FIXME: or should this be something else? like in lowerCall?
2446 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getCapTable(DAG.getMachineFunction());
2447 auto Addr = getDataFromCapTable(N, SDLoc(N), GlobalTy, DAG,
2448 DAG.getEntryNode(), PtrInfo);
2449 // Also handle the case where a ptrtoint is used on a global:
2450 if (Ty.isFatPointer())
2451 return Addr;
2452 assert(GlobalTy == CapType && Ty == MVT::i64 && "Should only have a ptrtoint node here");
2453 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRTOINT, SDLoc(N), Ty, Addr);
2454 } else {
2455 llvm::errs() << "Not using capability table for " << GV->getName() << "\n";
2456#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
2457 GV->dump();
2458#endif
2459 assert(false && "SHOULD HAVE USED CAP TABLE");
2460 }
2461 }
2462
2463 if (isCheriPointer(GV->getType(), &DAG.getDataLayout()))
2464 Ty = MVT::i64;
2465 SDValue Global;
2466
2467 if (!isPositionIndependent()) {
2468 const MipsTargetObjectFile *TLOF =
2469 static_cast<const MipsTargetObjectFile *>(
2470 getTargetMachine().getObjFileLowering());
2471 const GlobalObject *GO = GV->getBaseObject();
2472 if (GO && TLOF->IsGlobalInSmallSection(GO, getTargetMachine())) {
2473 // %gp_rel relocation
2474 Global = getAddrGPRel(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN64());
2475 } else {
2476 // %hi/%lo relocation
2477 Global = Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
2478 // %highest/%higher/%hi/%lo relocation
2479 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
2480 }
2481 } else {
2482
2483 // Every other architecture would use shouldAssumeDSOLocal in here, but
2484 // mips is special.
2485 // * In PIC code mips requires got loads even for local statics!
2486 // * To save on got entries, for local statics the got entry contains the
2487 // page and an additional add instruction takes care of the low bits.
2488 // * It is legal to access a hidden symbol with a non hidden undefined,
2489 // so one cannot guarantee that all access to a hidden symbol will know
2490 // it is hidden.
2491 // * Mips linkers don't support creating a page and a full got entry for
2492 // the same symbol.
2493 // * Given all that, we have to use a full got entry for hidden symbols :-(
2494 if (GV->hasLocalLinkage() && !HugeGOT)
2495 Global = getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(), GV->isThreadLocal());
2496 else if (LargeGOT || HugeGOT)
2497 Global = getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(
2498 N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_HI16, MipsII::MO_GOT_LO16,
2499 DAG.getEntryNode(),
2500 MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()), GV->isThreadLocal());
2501 else if (GV->hasInternalLinkage() || (GV->hasLocalLinkage() && !isa<Function>(GV)))
2502 Global = getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(), GV->isThreadLocal());
2503 else
2504 Global = getAddrGlobal(
2505 N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG,
2506 (ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()) ? MipsII::MO_GOT_DISP : MipsII::MO_GOT,
2507 DAG.getEntryNode(), MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()), GV->isThreadLocal());
2508 }
2509
2510 if (isCheriPointer(GV->getType(), &DAG.getDataLayout())) {
2511 assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
2512 // Allow compiling some LLVM IR generated for cap-table:
2513 if (isa<Function>(GV) || GV->getType()->getElementType()->isFunctionTy()) {
2514 // Derive function pointers from PCC instead of $ddc
2515 Global = setPccOffset(DAG, SDLoc(N), Global);
2516 } else {
2517 Global = cFromDDC(DAG, SDLoc(N), Global);
2518 }
2519 StringRef Name = GV->getName();
2520 if (!SkipGlobalBounds &&
2521 !isa<Function>(GV) &&
2522 !GV->hasWeakLinkage() &&
2523 !GV->hasWeakAnyLinkage() &&
2524 !GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage() &&
2525 !GV->hasSection() &&
2526 !Name.startswith("__start_") &&
2527 !Name.startswith("__stop_")) {
2528 if (GV->hasInternalLinkage() || GV->hasLocalLinkage()) {
2529 uint64_t SizeBytes = DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(GV->getValueType());
2530 Global =
2531 setBounds(DAG, Global, SizeBytes, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
2532 } else {
2533 const Module &M = *GV->getParent();
2534 std::string Name = (Twine(".size.")+GV->getName()).str();
2535 GlobalVariable *SizeGV = M.getGlobalVariable(Name);
2536 Type *I64 = Type::getInt64Ty(*DAG.getContext());
2537 if (!SizeGV) {
2538 SizeGV = new GlobalVariable(const_cast<Module&>(M),
2539 I64, /*isConstant*/true,
2540 GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage, ConstantInt::get(I64, 0),
2541 Twine(".size.")+GV->getName());
2542 SizeGV->setSection(".global_sizes");
2543 }
2544 SDValue Size = DAG.getGlobalAddress(SizeGV, SDLoc(Global), MVT::i64);
2545 Size = DAG.getLoad(MVT::i64, SDLoc(Global), DAG.getEntryNode(), Size,
2546 MachinePointerInfo(SizeGV));
2547 Global = setBounds(DAG, Global, Size, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
2548 }
2549 }
2550 }
2551 return Global;
2552}
2553
2554SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerBlockAddress(SDValue Op,
2555 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2556 BlockAddressSDNode *N = cast<BlockAddressSDNode>(Op);
2557 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType();
2558 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
2559
2560 if (!isPositionIndependent())
2561 return Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
2562 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
2563
2564 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable()) {
2565 if (N->getBlockAddress()->getFunction() != &MF.getFunction())
2566 report_fatal_error(
2567 "Should only get a blockaddress for the current function");
2568 auto BANode = DAG.getTargetBlockAddress(N->getBlockAddress(), MVT::i64,
2569 N->getOffset());
2570 // TODO: add the offset as another node?
2571 assert(N->getOffset() == 0 && "nonzero offset is not supported");
2572 // auto Offset = DAG.getConstant(N->getOffset(), SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
2573 return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(Mips::PseudoPccRelativeAddress, SDLoc(N),
2574 CapType, BANode),
2575 0);
2576 }
2577 // XXXAR: keep supporting the legacy ABI for now
2578 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
2579 Ty = MVT::i64;
2580 auto Result = getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(),
2581 /*IsForTls=*/false);
2582 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
2583 Result = setPccOffset(DAG, SDLoc(N), Result);
2584 return Result;
2585}
2586
2587SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
2588lowerGlobalTLSAddress(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const
2589{
2590 // FIXME: this needs to be revisited for cap-table
2591 // assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
2592
2593 // If the relocation model is PIC, use the General Dynamic TLS Model or
2594 // Local Dynamic TLS model, otherwise use the Initial Exec or
2595 // Local Exec TLS Model.
2596
2597 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
2598 if (DAG.getTarget().useEmulatedTLS())
2599 return LowerToTLSEmulatedModel(GA, DAG);
2600
2601 SDLoc DL(GA);
2602 const GlobalValue *GV = GA->getGlobal();
2603 TLSModel::Model model = getTargetMachine().getTLSModel(GV);
2604
2605 if (Subtarget.getABI().IsCheriPureCap() && Subtarget.useCheriCapTls()) {
2606 const Type *GVTy = GV->getType();
2607 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(GVTy)) {
2608 EVT OffsetVT = getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
2609 GVTy->getPointerAddressSpace());
2610 EVT CapVT = CapType;
2611
2612 if (model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic || model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) {
2613 // General Dynamic and Local Dynamic TLS Model.
2614 unsigned HiFlag, LoFlag;
2615 if (model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic) {
2616 HiFlag = MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TLSGD_HI16;
2617 LoFlag = MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TLSGD_LO16;
2618 } else {
2619 HiFlag = MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TLSLDM_HI16;
2620 LoFlag = MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TLSLDM_LO16;
2621 }
2622
2623 SDValue Argument = getCapToCapTable(GA, DL, DAG, HiFlag, LoFlag, 0,
2624 MipsISD::TlsHi);
2625 // Set bounds to sizeof(tls_index)
2626 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats)
2627 addGlobalsCSetBoundsStats(GV, DAG, "set bounds on tls_index",
2628 DL.getDebugLoc());
2629 Argument = setBounds(DAG, Argument, 16, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
2630 Type *CapTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(*DAG.getContext(),
2631 GVTy->getPointerAddressSpace());
2632
2633 SDValue TlsGetAddr = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol("__tls_get_addr");
2634
2635 ArgListTy Args;
2636 ArgListEntry Entry;
2637 Entry.Node = Argument;
2638 Entry.Ty = CapTy;
2639 Args.push_back(Entry);
2640
2641 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2642 CLI.setDebugLoc(DL)
2643 .setChain(DAG.getEntryNode())
2644 .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, CapTy, TlsGetAddr, std::move(Args));
2645 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = LowerCallTo(CLI);
2646
2647 SDValue Ret = CallResult.first;
2648
2649 if (model != TLSModel::LocalDynamic)
2650 return Ret;
2651
2652 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, OffsetVT, 0,
2653 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_HI);
2654 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, OffsetVT, TGAHi);
2655 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, OffsetVT, 0,
2656 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_LO);
2657 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, OffsetVT, TGALo);
2658 SDValue Add = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, OffsetVT, Hi, Lo);
2659 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRADD, DL, CapVT, Ret, Add);
2660 }
2661
2662 SDValue Offset;
2663 if (model == TLSModel::InitialExec) {
2664 // Initial Exec TLS Model
2665 auto PtrInfo =
2666 MachinePointerInfo::getCapTable(DAG.getMachineFunction());
2667 Offset =
2668 getFromCapTable(GA, DL, OffsetVT, DAG, DAG.getEntryNode(), PtrInfo,
2669 MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TPREL_HI16,
2670 MipsII::MO_CAPTAB_TPREL_LO16, 0, MipsISD::TlsHi);
2671 } else {
2672 // Local Exec TLS Model
2673 assert(model == TLSModel::LocalExec);
2674 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, OffsetVT, 0,
2675 MipsII::MO_TPREL_HI);
2676 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, OffsetVT, 0,
2677 MipsII::MO_TPREL_LO);
2678 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, OffsetVT, TGAHi);
2679 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, OffsetVT, TGALo);
2680 Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, OffsetVT, Hi, Lo);
2681 }
2682
2683 SDValue ThreadPointer = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapThreadPointer,
2684 DL, CapVT);
2685 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRADD, DL, CapVT, ThreadPointer, Offset);
2686 } else {
2687#if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP)
2688 GV->dump();
2689#endif
2690 report_fatal_error("SHOULD HAVE USED CAP TLS for " + GV->getName());
2691 }
2692 }
2693
2694 // NOTE: AS0 is okay since we are using the legacy ABI
2695 assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTls());
2696 EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), 0);
2697
2698 if (model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic || model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) {
2699 // General Dynamic and Local Dynamic TLS Model.
2700 unsigned Flag = (model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) ? MipsII::MO_TLSLDM
2701 : MipsII::MO_TLSGD;
2702
2703 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, Flag);
2704 SDValue Argument = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Wrapper, DL, PtrVT,
2705 getGlobalReg(DAG, PtrVT, /*IsForTls=*/true), TGA);
2706 unsigned PtrSize = PtrVT.getSizeInBits();
2707 Type *TlsGetAddrArgAndRetTy = Type::getIntNTy(*DAG.getContext(), PtrSize);
2708
2709 SDValue TlsGetAddr = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol("__tls_get_addr");
2710
2711 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
2712 Argument = cFromDDC(DAG, DL, Argument);
2713 // Set bounds to sizeof(tls_index)
2714 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats)
2715 addGlobalsCSetBoundsStats(GV, DAG, "set bounds on tls_index",
2716 DL.getDebugLoc());
2717 Argument = setBounds(DAG, Argument, 16, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
2718 // In the pure-capability ABI __tls_get_addr takes and returns capabilities
2719 TlsGetAddrArgAndRetTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(*DAG.getContext(), 200);
2720 }
2721
2722 ArgListTy Args;
2723 ArgListEntry Entry;
2724 Entry.Node = Argument;
2725 Entry.Ty = TlsGetAddrArgAndRetTy;
2726 Args.push_back(Entry);
2727
2728 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2729 CLI.setDebugLoc(DL)
2730 .setChain(DAG.getEntryNode())
2731 .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, TlsGetAddrArgAndRetTy, TlsGetAddr, std::move(Args));
2732 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = LowerCallTo(CLI);
2733
2734 SDValue Ret = CallResult.first;
2735 // Convert back to an integer value for the legacy ABI:
2736 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
2737 auto GetAddr = DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get, DL, PtrVT);
2738 Ret = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, MVT::i64, GetAddr, Ret);
2739 }
2740
2741 if (model != TLSModel::LocalDynamic)
2742 return Ret;
2743
2744 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0,
2745 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_HI);
2746 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, PtrVT, TGAHi);
2747 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0,
2748 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_LO);
2749 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT, TGALo);
2750 SDValue Add = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Ret);
2751 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Add, Lo);
2752 }
2753
2754 SDValue Offset;
2755 if (model == TLSModel::InitialExec) {
2756 // Initial Exec TLS Model
2757 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0,
2758 MipsII::MO_GOTTPREL);
2759 TGA = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Wrapper, DL, PtrVT, getGlobalReg(DAG, PtrVT, true),
2760 TGA);
2761 Offset =
2762 DAG.getLoad(PtrVT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), TGA, MachinePointerInfo());
2763 } else {
2764 // Local Exec TLS Model
2765 assert(model == TLSModel::LocalExec);
2766 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0,
2767 MipsII::MO_TPREL_HI);
2768 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0,
2769 MipsII::MO_TPREL_LO);
2770 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, PtrVT, TGAHi);
2771 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT, TGALo);
2772 Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Lo);
2773 }
2774
2775 SDValue ThreadPointer = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ThreadPointer, DL, PtrVT);
2776 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, ThreadPointer, Offset);
2777}

2779SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
2780lowerJumpTable(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const
2781{
2782 JumpTableSDNode *N = cast<JumpTableSDNode>(Op);
2783 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType();
2784
2785 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable()) {
2786 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getCapTable(DAG.getMachineFunction());
2787 return getDataFromCapTable(N, SDLoc(N), CapType, DAG, DAG.getEntryNode(),
2788 PtrInfo);
2789 }
2790
2791 if (!isPositionIndependent())
2792 return Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
2793 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
2794
2795 if (LargeGOT)
2796 return getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_HI16,
2797 MipsII::MO_GOT_LO16, DAG.getEntryNode(),
2798 MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()), /*IsForTls=*/false);
2799
2800 return getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(), /*IsForTls=*/false);
2801}
2802
2803SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
2804lowerConstantPool(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const
2805{
2806 ConstantPoolSDNode *N = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(Op);
2807 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType();
2808
2809 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable()) {
2810 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getCapTable(DAG.getMachineFunction());
2811 assert(Ty.isFatPointer());
2812 auto Result = getDataFromCapTable(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, DAG.getEntryNode(), PtrInfo);
2813 assert(Result.getValueType() == Ty);
2814 return Result;
2815 }
2816
2817 if (!isPositionIndependent()) {
2818 const MipsTargetObjectFile *TLOF =
2819 static_cast<const MipsTargetObjectFile *>(
2820 getTargetMachine().getObjFileLowering());
2821
2822 if (TLOF->IsConstantInSmallSection(DAG.getDataLayout(), N->getConstVal(),
2823 getTargetMachine()))
2824 // %gp_rel relocation
2825 return getAddrGPRel(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN64());
2826
2827 return Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
2828 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
2829 }
2830
2831 return getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(),
2832 /*IsForTls=*/false);
2833}
2834
2835SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerVASTART(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2836 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
2837 MipsFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
2838
2839 SDLoc DL(Op);
2840 SDValue FI = DAG.getFrameIndex(FuncInfo->getVarArgsFrameIndex(),
2841 getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout(),
2842 ABI.StackAddrSpace()));
2843
2844 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
2845 unsigned Reg = MF.addLiveIn(Mips::C13, getRegClassFor(CapType));
2846 // In the sandbox ABI, the va_start intrinsic will (to work around LLVM's
2847 // assumption that allocas are all in AS0) be an address space cast of the
2848 // alloca to AS 0. We need to extract the original operands.
2849 const Value *SV = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getValue();
2850 SV = SV->stripPointerCasts();
2851 assert(isCheriPointer(SV->getType(), &DAG.getDataLayout()));
2852 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
2853 SDValue CapAddr = Op.getOperand(1);
2854 FI = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Reg, CapType);
2855 return DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, FI, CapAddr, MachinePointerInfo(SV));
2856 }
2857
2858 // vastart just stores the address of the VarArgsFrameIndex slot into the
2859 // memory location argument.
2860 const Value *SV = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getValue();
2861 return DAG.getStore(Op.getOperand(0), DL, FI, Op.getOperand(1),
2862 MachinePointerInfo(SV));
2863}
2864
2865SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerVACOPY(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2866 // VACOPY lowering should only be custom with the sandbox ABI.
2867 assert(ABI.IsCheriPureCap());
2868
2869 SDValue Chain = Op->getOperand(0);
2870 SDValue Dest = Op->getOperand(1);
2871 SDValue Src = Op->getOperand(2);
2872 SDLoc DL(Op);
2873 // The source is a pointer to the existing va_list
2874 Src = DAG.getLoad(CapType, DL, Chain, Src, MachinePointerInfo());
2875 return DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Src, Dest, MachinePointerInfo());
2876}
2877
2878SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerVAARG(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2879 SDNode *Node = Op.getNode();
2880 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
2881 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0);
2882 SDValue VAListPtr = Node->getOperand(1);
2883 unsigned Align = Node->getConstantOperandVal(3);
2884 const Value *SV = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Node->getOperand(2))->getValue();
2885 SDLoc DL(Node);
2886 unsigned ArgSlotSizeInBytes = (ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()) ? 8 : 4;
2887
2888 SDValue VAListLoad =
2889 DAG.getLoad(getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
2890 DAG.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace()),
2891 DL, Chain, VAListPtr, MachinePointerInfo(SV));
2892 SDValue VAList = VAListLoad;
2893
2894 // Re-align the pointer if necessary.
2895 // It should only ever be necessary for 64-bit types on O32 since the minimum
2896 // argument alignment is the same as the maximum type alignment for N32/N64.
2897 //
2898 // FIXME: We currently align too often. The code generator doesn't notice
2899 // when the pointer is still aligned from the last va_arg (or pair of
2900 // va_args for the i64 on O32 case).
2901 if (Align > getMinStackArgumentAlignment()) {
2902 assert(((Align & (Align-1)) == 0) && "Expected Align to be a power of 2");
2903
2904 VAList = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2905 DAG.getConstant(Align - 1, DL, VAList.getValueType()));
2906
2907 VAList = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2908 DAG.getConstant(-(int64_t)Align, DL,
2909 VAList.getValueType()));
2910 }
2911
2912 // Increment the pointer, VAList, to the next vaarg.
2913 auto &TD = DAG.getDataLayout();
2914 unsigned ArgSizeInBytes =
2915 TD.getTypeAllocSize(VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
2916 SDValue Tmp3 =
2917 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList,
2918 DAG.getConstant(alignTo(ArgSizeInBytes, ArgSlotSizeInBytes),
2919 DL, VAList.getValueType()));
2920 // Store the incremented VAList to the legalized pointer
2921 Chain = DAG.getStore(VAListLoad.getValue(1), DL, Tmp3, VAListPtr,
2922 MachinePointerInfo(SV));
2923
2924 // In big-endian mode we must adjust the pointer when the load size is smaller
2925 // than the argument slot size. We must also reduce the known alignment to
2926 // match. For example in the N64 ABI, we must add 4 bytes to the offset to get
2927 // the correct half of the slot, and reduce the alignment from 8 (slot
2928 // alignment) down to 4 (type alignment).
2929 if (!Subtarget.isLittle() && ArgSizeInBytes < ArgSlotSizeInBytes) {
2930 unsigned Adjustment = ArgSlotSizeInBytes - ArgSizeInBytes;
2931 VAList = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VAListPtr.getValueType(), VAList,
2932 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Adjustment, DL));
2933 }
2934 // Load the actual argument out of the pointer VAList
2935 return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, Chain, VAList, MachinePointerInfo());
2936}
2937
2938static SDValue lowerFCOPYSIGN32(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2939 bool HasExtractInsert) {
2940 EVT TyX = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2941 EVT TyY = Op.getOperand(1).getValueType();
2942 SDLoc DL(Op);
2943 SDValue Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
2944 SDValue Const31 = DAG.getConstant(31, DL, MVT::i32);
2945 SDValue Res;
2946
2947 // If operand is of type f64, extract the upper 32-bit. Otherwise, bitcast it
2948 // to i32.
2949 SDValue X = (TyX == MVT::f32) ?
2950 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0)) :
2951 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0),
2952 Const1);
2953 SDValue Y = (TyY == MVT::f32) ?
2954 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(1)) :
2955 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(1),
2956 Const1);
2957
2958 if (HasExtractInsert) {
2959 // ext E, Y, 31, 1 ; extract bit31 of Y
2960 // ins X, E, 31, 1 ; insert extracted bit at bit31 of X
2961 SDValue E = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ext, DL, MVT::i32, Y, Const31, Const1);
2962 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i32, E, Const31, Const1, X);
2963 } else {
2964 // sll SllX, X, 1
2965 // srl SrlX, SllX, 1
2966 // srl SrlY, Y, 31
2967 // sll SllY, SrlX, 31
2968 // or Or, SrlX, SllY
2969 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, X, Const1);
2970 SDValue SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, SllX, Const1);
2971 SDValue SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, Y, Const31);
2972 SDValue SllY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, SrlY, Const31);
2973 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i32, SrlX, SllY);
2974 }
2975
2976 if (TyX == MVT::f32)
2977 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), Res);
2978
2979 SDValue LowX = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
2980 Op.getOperand(0),
2981 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
2982 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, LowX, Res);
2983}
2984
2985static SDValue lowerFCOPYSIGN64(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2986 bool HasExtractInsert) {
2987 unsigned WidthX = Op.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits();
2988 unsigned WidthY = Op.getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits();
2989 EVT TyX = MVT::getIntegerVT(WidthX), TyY = MVT::getIntegerVT(WidthY);
2990 SDLoc DL(Op);
2991 SDValue Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
2992
2993 // Bitcast to integer nodes.
2994 SDValue X = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, TyX, Op.getOperand(0));
2995 SDValue Y = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, TyY, Op.getOperand(1));
2996
2997 if (HasExtractInsert) {
2998 // ext E, Y, width(Y) - 1, 1 ; extract bit width(Y)-1 of Y
2999 // ins X, E, width(X) - 1, 1 ; insert extracted bit at bit width(X)-1 of X
3000 SDValue E = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ext, DL, TyY, Y,
3001 DAG.getConstant(WidthY - 1, DL, MVT::i32), Const1);
3002
3003 if (WidthX > WidthY)
3004 E = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, TyX, E);
3005 else if (WidthY > WidthX)
3006 E = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, TyX, E);
3007
3008 SDValue I = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, TyX, E,
3009 DAG.getConstant(WidthX - 1, DL, MVT::i32), Const1,
3010 X);
3011 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), I);
3012 }
3013
3014 // (d)sll SllX, X, 1
3015 // (d)srl SrlX, SllX, 1
3016 // (d)srl SrlY, Y, width(Y)-1
3017 // (d)sll SllY, SrlX, width(Y)-1
3018 // or Or, SrlX, SllY
3019 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, TyX, X, Const1);
3020 SDValue SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, TyX, SllX, Const1);
3021 SDValue SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, TyY, Y,
3022 DAG.getConstant(WidthY - 1, DL, MVT::i32));
3023
3024 if (WidthX > WidthY)
3025 SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, TyX, SrlY);
3026 else if (WidthY > WidthX)
3027 SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, TyX, SrlY);
3028
3029 SDValue SllY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, TyX, SrlY,
3030 DAG.getConstant(WidthX - 1, DL, MVT::i32));
3031 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, TyX, SrlX, SllY);
3032 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), Or);
3033}

3036MipsTargetLowering::lowerFCOPYSIGN(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3037 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit())
3038 return lowerFCOPYSIGN64(Op, DAG, Subtarget.hasExtractInsert());
3039
3040 return lowerFCOPYSIGN32(Op, DAG, Subtarget.hasExtractInsert());

3042
3043static SDValue lowerFABS32(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3044 bool HasExtractInsert) {
3045 SDLoc DL(Op);
3046 SDValue Res, Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
3047
3048 // If operand is of type f64, extract the upper 32-bit. Otherwise, bitcast it
3049 // to i32.
3050 SDValue X = (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f32)
3051 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0))
3052 : DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
3053 Op.getOperand(0), Const1);
3054
3055 // Clear MSB.
3056 if (HasExtractInsert)
3057 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i32,
3058 DAG.getRegister(Mips::ZERO, MVT::i32),
3059 DAG.getConstant(31, DL, MVT::i32), Const1, X);
3060 else {
3061 // TODO: Provide DAG patterns which transform (and x, cst)
3062 // back to a (shl (srl x (clz cst)) (clz cst)) sequence.
3063 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, X, Const1);
3064 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, SllX, Const1);
3065 }
3066
3067 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f32)
3068 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Res);
3069
3070 // FIXME: For mips32r2, the sequence of (BuildPairF64 (ins (ExtractElementF64
3071 // Op 1), $zero, 31 1) (ExtractElementF64 Op 0)) and the Op has one use, we
3072 // should be able to drop the usage of mfc1/mtc1 and rewrite the register in
3073 // place.
3074 SDValue LowX =
3075 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0),
3076 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
3077 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, LowX, Res);
3078}
3079
3080static SDValue lowerFABS64(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3081 bool HasExtractInsert) {
3082 SDLoc DL(Op);
3083 SDValue Res, Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
3084
3085 // Bitcast to integer node.
3086 SDValue X = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i64, Op.getOperand(0));
3087
3088 // Clear MSB.
3089 if (HasExtractInsert)
3090 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i64,
3091 DAG.getRegister(Mips::ZERO_64, MVT::i64),
3092 DAG.getConstant(63, DL, MVT::i32), Const1, X);
3093 else {
3094 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, X, Const1);
3095 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, SllX, Const1);
3096 }
3097
3098 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f64, Res);
3099}

3108SDValue MipsTargetLowering::
3109lowerFRAMEADDR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3110 // check the depth
3111 if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue() != 0) {
3112 DAG.getContext()->emitError(
3113 "return address can be determined only for current frame");
3114 return SDValue();
3115 }
3116
3117 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
3118 MFI.setFrameAddressIsTaken(true);
3119 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
3120 SDLoc DL(Op);
3121 SDValue FrameAddr =
3122 DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, ABI.GetFramePtr(), VT);
3123 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
3124 assert(VT == CapType);
3125 }
3126 return FrameAddr;
3127}
3128
3129SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerRETURNADDR(SDValue Op,
3130 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3131 if (verifyReturnAddressArgumentIsConstant(Op, DAG))
3132 return SDValue();
3133
3134 // check the depth
3135 if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue() != 0) {
3136 DAG.getContext()->emitError(
3137 "return address can be determined only for current frame");
3138 return SDValue();
3139 }
3140
3141 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
3142 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
3143 MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3144 unsigned RA = ABI.GetReturnAddress();
3145 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
3146 assert(VT == CapType);
3147 }
3148 MFI.setReturnAddressIsTaken(true);
3149
3150 // Return RA, which contains the return address. Mark it an implicit live-in.
3151 unsigned Reg = MF.addLiveIn(RA, getRegClassFor(VT));
3152 return DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Op), Reg, VT);
3153}
3154
3155// An EH_RETURN is the result of lowering llvm.eh.return which in turn is
3156// generated from __builtin_eh_return (offset, handler)
3157// The effect of this is to adjust the stack pointer by "offset"
3158// and then branch to "handler".
3159SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerEH_RETURN(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG)
3160 const {
3161 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
3162 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
3163
3164 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable())
3165 report_fatal_error("MipsTargetLowering::lowerEH_RETURN needs fixing!");
3166 unsigned AS = getExceptionPointerAS();
3167
3168 MipsFI->setCallsEhReturn();
3169 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
3170 SDValue Offset = Op.getOperand(1);
3171 SDValue Handler = Op.getOperand(2);
3172 SDLoc DL(Op);
3173 EVT Ty = ABI.IsN64() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
3174
3175 // Store stack offset in V1, store jump target in V0. Glue CopyToReg and
3176 // EH_RETURN nodes, so that instructions are emitted back-to-back.
3177 unsigned OffsetReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::V1_64 : Mips::V1;
3178 unsigned AddrReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::V0_64 : Mips::V0;
3179 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, OffsetReg, Offset, SDValue());
3180 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, AddrReg, Handler, Chain.getValue(1));
3181 return DAG.getNode(
3182 MipsISD::EH_RETURN, DL, MVT::Other, Chain, DAG.getRegister(OffsetReg, Ty),
3183 DAG.getRegister(AddrReg, getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout(), AS)),
3184 Chain.getValue(1));
3185}

3191 unsigned SType = 0;

3196
3197SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerShiftLeftParts(SDValue Op,
3198 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3199 SDLoc DL(Op);
3200 MVT VT = Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
3201
3202 SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0), Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
3203 SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
3204 // if shamt < (VT.bits):
3205 // lo = (shl lo, shamt)
3206 // hi = (or (shl hi, shamt) (srl (srl lo, 1), ~shamt))
3207 // else:
3208 // lo = 0
3209 // hi = (shl lo, shamt[4:0])
3210 SDValue Not = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt,
3211 DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, MVT::i32));
3212 SDValue ShiftRight1Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo,
3213 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT));
3214 SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, ShiftRight1Lo, Not);
3215 SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
3216 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo);
3217 SDValue ShiftLeftLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
3218 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt,
3219 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits(), DL, MVT::i32));
3220 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond,
3221 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ShiftLeftLo);
3222 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, ShiftLeftLo, Or);
3223
3224 SDValue Ops[2] = {Lo, Hi};
3225 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
3226}
3227
3228SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerShiftRightParts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3229 bool IsSRA) const {
3230 SDLoc DL(Op);
3231 SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0), Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
3232 SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
3233 MVT VT = Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
3234
3235 // if shamt < (VT.bits):
3236 // lo = (or (shl (shl hi, 1), ~shamt) (srl lo, shamt))
3237 // if isSRA:
3238 // hi = (sra hi, shamt)
3239 // else:
3240 // hi = (srl hi, shamt)
3241 // else:
3242 // if isSRA:
3243 // lo = (sra hi, shamt[4:0])
3244 // hi = (sra hi, 31)
3245 // else:
3246 // lo = (srl hi, shamt[4:0])
3247 // hi = 0
3248 SDValue Not = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt,
3249 DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, MVT::i32));
3250 SDValue ShiftLeft1Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi,
3251 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT));
3252 SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, ShiftLeft1Hi, Not);
3253 SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
3254 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo);
3255 SDValue ShiftRightHi = DAG.getNode(IsSRA ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL,
3256 DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
3257 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt,
3258 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits(), DL, MVT::i32));
3259 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Hi,
3260 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits() - 1, DL, VT));
3261
3262 if (!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32())) {
3263 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
3264 return DAG.getNode(Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? Mips::PseudoD_SELECT_I64
3265 : Mips::PseudoD_SELECT_I,
3266 DL, VTList, Cond, ShiftRightHi,
3267 IsSRA ? Ext : DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), Or,
3268 ShiftRightHi);
3269 }
3270
3271 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, ShiftRightHi, Or);
3272 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond,
3273 IsSRA ? Ext : DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ShiftRightHi);
3274
3275 SDValue Ops[2] = {Lo, Hi};
3276 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
3277}

3279static SDValue createLoadLR(unsigned Opc, SelectionDAG &DAG, LoadSDNode *LD,
3280 SDValue Chain, SDValue Src, unsigned Offset) {
3281 SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr();
3282 EVT VT = LD->getValueType(0), MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
3283 SDLoc DL(LD);
3284 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other);
3285
3286 if (Offset)
3287 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Ptr, Offset);
3288
3289 SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Ptr, Src };
3290 return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, VTList, Ops, MemVT,
3291 LD->getMemOperand());
3292}
3293// Expand an unaligned 32 or 64-bit integer load node.
3294SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerLOAD(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3295 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
3296 EVT MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
3297
3298 if (Subtarget.systemSupportsUnalignedAccess(LD->getAddressSpace()))
3299 return Op;
3300
3301 // We don't handle capability-releative loads here, so make sure that we
3302 // don't encounter them!
3303 assert(!MemVT.isFatPointer());
3304
3305 // Return if load is aligned or if MemVT is neither i32 nor i64.
3306 if ((LD->getAlignment() >= MemVT.getSizeInBits() / 8)) {
3307 return SDValue();
3308 } else if (Subtarget.isABI_CheriPureCap()) {
3309 // Can't use LWL/LWR in pure capability ABI -> fall back to generic code
3310 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> P = expandUnalignedLoad(LD, DAG);
3311 return DAG.getMergeValues({P.first, P.second}, SDLoc(LD));
3312 } else if (((MemVT != MVT::i32) && (MemVT != MVT::i64))) {
3313 return SDValue();
3314 }
3315
3316 bool IsLittle = Subtarget.isLittle();
3317 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
3318 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
3319 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain(), Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
3320
3321 assert((VT == MVT::i32) || (VT == MVT::i64));
3322
3323 assert(!Subtarget.isABI_CheriPureCap() && "LWL/LWR not supported in purecap");
3324
3325 // Expand
3326 // (set dst, (i64 (load baseptr)))
3327 // to
3328 // (set tmp, (ldl (add baseptr, 7), undef))
3329 // (set dst, (ldr baseptr, tmp))
3330 if ((VT == MVT::i64) && (ExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)) {
3331 SDValue LDL = createLoadLR(MipsISD::LDL, DAG, LD, Chain, Undef,
3332 IsLittle ? 7 : 0);
3333 return createLoadLR(MipsISD::LDR, DAG, LD, LDL.getValue(1), LDL,
3334 IsLittle ? 0 : 7);
3335 }
3336
3337 SDValue LWL = createLoadLR(MipsISD::LWL, DAG, LD, Chain, Undef,
3338 IsLittle ? 3 : 0);
3339 SDValue LWR = createLoadLR(MipsISD::LWR, DAG, LD, LWL.getValue(1), LWL,
3340 IsLittle ? 0 : 3);
3341
3342 // Expand
3343 // (set dst, (i32 (load baseptr))) or
3344 // (set dst, (i64 (sextload baseptr))) or
3345 // (set dst, (i64 (extload baseptr)))
3346 // to
3347 // (set tmp, (lwl (add baseptr, 3), undef))
3348 // (set dst, (lwr baseptr, tmp))
3349 if ((VT == MVT::i32) || (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) ||
3350 (ExtType == ISD::EXTLOAD))
3351 return LWR;
3352
3353 assert((VT == MVT::i64) && (ExtType == ISD::ZEXTLOAD));
3354
3355 // Expand
3356 // (set dst, (i64 (zextload baseptr)))
3357 // to
3358 // (set tmp0, (lwl (add baseptr, 3), undef))
3359 // (set tmp1, (lwr baseptr, tmp0))
3360 // (set tmp2, (shl tmp1, 32))
3361 // (set dst, (srl tmp2, 32))
3362 SDLoc DL(LD);
3363 SDValue Const32 = DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32);
3364 SDValue SLL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, LWR, Const32);
3365 SDValue SRL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, SLL, Const32);
3366 SDValue Ops[] = { SRL, LWR.getValue(1) };
3367 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
3368}

3370static SDValue createStoreLR(unsigned Opc, SelectionDAG &DAG, StoreSDNode *SD,
3371 SDValue Chain, unsigned Offset) {
3372 SDValue Ptr = SD->getBasePtr(), Value = SD->getValue();
3373 EVT MemVT = SD->getMemoryVT();
3374 SDLoc DL(SD);
3375 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other);
3376
3377 if (Offset)
3378 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Ptr, Offset);
3379
3380 SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Value, Ptr };
3381 return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, VTList, Ops, MemVT,
3382 SD->getMemOperand());
3383}
3384
3385// Expand an unaligned 32 or 64-bit integer store node.
3386static SDValue lowerUnalignedIntStore(StoreSDNode *SD, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3387 bool IsLittle, bool IsCHERI) {
3388 SDValue Value = SD->getValue(), Chain = SD->getChain();
3389 EVT VT = Value.getValueType();
3390 SDValue BasePtr = SD->getBasePtr();
3391
3392 // CHERI doesn't have a capability version of SDR / SDL, so we turn this into
3393 // a sequence of byte stores and shifts.
3394 if (IsCHERI && (BasePtr->getValueType(0).isFatPointer())) {
3395 SDLoc DL(SD);
3396 EVT MemVT = SD->getMemoryVT();
3397 SDValue Store;
3398 int Size = (MemVT.getSizeInBits() / 8);
3399 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
3400 // CHERI is big endian. We'll write the lowest bytes at the end of the
3401 // word first
3402 for (int Offset=Size-1 ; Offset>=0 ; Offset-=1) {
3403 // Address to store this byte
3404 SDValue Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, BasePtr, Offset);
3405 // Store the next byte
3406 Store = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, DL, Value, Ptr,
3407 MVT::i8, SD->getMemOperand());
3408 Ops.push_back(Store);
3409 Chain = Store;
3410 // Shift the value
3411 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Value, DAG.getConstant(8, DL, VT));
3412 }
3413 return Store;
3414 }
3415
3416 // Expand
3417 // (store val, baseptr) or
3418 // (truncstore val, baseptr)
3419 // to
3420 // (swl val, (add baseptr, 3))
3421 // (swr val, baseptr)
3422 if ((VT == MVT::i32) || SD->isTruncatingStore()) {
3423 SDValue SWL = createStoreLR(MipsISD::SWL, DAG, SD, Chain,
3424 IsLittle ? 3 : 0);
3425 return createStoreLR(MipsISD::SWR, DAG, SD, SWL, IsLittle ? 0 : 3);
3426 }
3427
3428 assert(VT == MVT::i64);
3429
3430 // Expand
3431 // (store val, baseptr)
3432 // to
3433 // (sdl val, (add baseptr, 7))
3434 // (sdr val, baseptr)
3435 SDValue SDL = createStoreLR(MipsISD::SDL, DAG, SD, Chain, IsLittle ? 7 : 0);
3436 return createStoreLR(MipsISD::SDR, DAG, SD, SDL, IsLittle ? 0 : 7);
3437}

3439// Lower (store (fp_to_sint $fp) $ptr) to (store (TruncIntFP $fp), $ptr).
3440static SDValue lowerFP_TO_SINT_STORE(StoreSDNode *SD, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3441 bool SingleFloat) {
3442 SDValue Val = SD->getValue();
3443
3444 if (Val.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_TO_SINT ||
3445 (Val.getValueSizeInBits() > 32 && SingleFloat))
3446 return SDValue();
3447
3448 EVT FPTy = EVT::getFloatingPointVT(Val.getValueSizeInBits());
3449 SDValue Tr = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TruncIntFP, SDLoc(Val), FPTy,
3450 Val.getOperand(0));
3451 return DAG.getStore(SD->getChain(), SDLoc(SD), Tr, SD->getBasePtr(),
3452 SD->getPointerInfo(), SD->getAlignment(),
3453 SD->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
3454}
3455
3456SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerSTORE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3457 StoreSDNode *SD = cast<StoreSDNode>(Op);
3458 EVT MemVT = SD->getMemoryVT();
3459 const SDValue Val = SD->getValue();
3460
3461 // If we're doing a capability-relative load or store of something smaller
3462 // than 64 bits, then we need to insert an anyext node to make the input
3463 // value an i64
3464 if (Subtarget.isCheri() && SD->isTruncatingStore() && Val.getValueType() == MVT::i32) {
3465 SDValue Chain = SD->getChain();
3466 SDValue BasePtr = SD->getBasePtr();
3467 SDLoc DL(Op);
3468 const SDValue ExtNode = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Val, DL, MVT::i64);
3469 return DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, DL, ExtNode, BasePtr, MemVT,
3470 SD->getMemOperand());
3471 }
3472
3473 // Lower unaligned integer stores.
3474 if (!Subtarget.systemSupportsUnalignedAccess(SD->getAddressSpace()) &&
3475 (SD->getAlignment() < MemVT.getSizeInBits() / 8) &&
3476 ((MemVT == MVT::i32) || (MemVT == MVT::i64)))
3477 return lowerUnalignedIntStore(SD, DAG, Subtarget.isLittle(),
3478 Subtarget.isCheri());
3479
3480 return lowerFP_TO_SINT_STORE(SD, DAG, Subtarget.isSingleFloat());
3481}

3504
3505SDValue
3506MipsTargetLowering::convertToPCCDerivedCap(SDValue TargetAddr, const SDLoc &dl,
3507 SelectionDAG &DAG,
3508 SDValue AdditionalOffset) const {
3509 // To get a pcc derived capability we can just do the equivalent of SetAddr
3510 auto GetPCC = DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_pcc_get, dl, MVT::i64);
3511 // TODO: it would be nice if we could just create a setaddr node here and
3512 // expand it later
3513 auto PCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, CapType, GetPCC);
3514 SDValue OffsetFromPCC;
3515 if (TargetAddr.getValueType() == MVT::i64) {
3516 // If addr is an i64: CIncOfset($pcc, $addr - CGetAddr($pcc))
3517 auto GetAddr =
3518 DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get, dl, MVT::i64);
3519 auto PCCAddrI64 =
3520 DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, MVT::i64, GetAddr, PCC);
3521 OffsetFromPCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, MVT::i64, TargetAddr, PCCAddrI64);
3522 } else {
3523 assert(TargetAddr.getValueType() == CapType);
3524 // If addr is a cap: CIncOfset($pcc, CSub($addr $pcc))
3525 auto CSub = DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_diff, dl, MVT::i64);
3526 OffsetFromPCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, MVT::i64, CSub,
3527 TargetAddr, PCC);
3528 }
3529 if (AdditionalOffset) {
3530 // We can't add the AdditionalOffset to either the source or target address
3531 // capability since prior to using CSub since it might cause it to become
3532 // unrepresentable. Instead add it to the computed OffsetFromPCC now.
3533 OffsetFromPCC =
3534 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i64, OffsetFromPCC, AdditionalOffset);
3535 }
3536 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRADD, dl, CapType, PCC, OffsetFromPCC);
3537}
3538
3539SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerBR_JT(SDValue Op,
3540 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3541 // FIXME: this is almost the same as the code in LegalizeDAG.cpp, can
3542 // I just adjust that to work for capabilities too?
3543
3544 assert(ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
3545
3546 SDLoc dl(Op);
3547 SDValue Chain = Op->getOperand(0);
3548 SDValue Table = Op->getOperand(1);
3549 SDValue Index = Op->getOperand(2);
3550
3551 const DataLayout &TD = DAG.getDataLayout();
3552 EVT PTy = getPointerTy(TD, 200);
3553 assert(PTy == CapType);
3554 unsigned EntrySize =
3555 DAG.getMachineFunction().getJumpTableInfo()->getEntrySize(TD);
3556 assert(EntrySize == 4);
3557 assert(isPowerOf2_64(EntrySize));
3558 // FIXME: or should this be something else? like in lowerCall?
3559 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getCapTable(DAG.getMachineFunction());
3560 SDValue Jumptable = getDataFromCapTable(
3561 cast<JumpTableSDNode>(Table.getNode()), dl, PTy, DAG, Chain, PtrInfo);
3562 // TODO: use a mul here and let the code later on convert it to a shift?
3563 Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, MVT::i64, Index,
3564 DAG.getConstant(Log2_32(EntrySize), dl, MVT::i64));
3565 EVT MemVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), EntrySize * 8);
3566 auto LoadAddr = DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRADD, dl, PTy, Jumptable, Index);
3567 SDValue JTEntryValue = DAG.getExtLoad(
3568 ISD::SEXTLOAD, dl, MVT::i64, Chain, LoadAddr,
3569 MachinePointerInfo::getJumpTable(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MemVT);
3570 Chain = JTEntryValue.getValue(1);
3571 assert(isJumpTableRelative());
3572 // Each jump table entry contains .4byte .LBB0_N - .LJTI0_0.
3573 // Since the jump table comes before .text this will generally be a positive
3574 // number that we can add to the address of the jump-table to get the
3575 // address of the basic block:
3576
3577 // TODO: use a smarter model for jump tables, this is just used because
3578 // there is existing infrastucture. Maybe use offset from beginning of func
3579 // instead?
3580
3581 // Addr is a data capability so won't have Permit_Execute so we have to derive
3582 // a new capability from PCC:
3583 // We use the jump table capability as the target address capability and
3584 // then add on the value loaded from the jump table to get the actual basic
3585 // block address:
3586 // addrof(BB) = addrof(JT) + *(JT[INDEX])
3587 // New PPC = CIncOffset, PCC, (addrof(BB) - addrof(PCC))
3588 // This can be done slightly more efficiently as:
3589 // New PPC = CIncOffset, PCC, (CSub(JT, PCC) + *(JT[INDEX]))
3590 // But not the following since it might cause JT to become unrepresentable:
3591 // New PPC = CIncOffset, PCC, (CSub(JT + *(JT[INDEX]), PCC))
3592 JTEntryValue = convertToPCCDerivedCap(Jumptable, dl, DAG, JTEntryValue);
3593 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BRIND, dl, MVT::Other, Chain, JTEntryValue);
3594}

3596//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3597// Calling Convention Implementation
3598//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3599
3600//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3601// TODO: Implement a generic logic using tblgen that can support this.
3602// Mips O32 ABI rules:
3603// ---
3604// i32 - Passed in A0, A1, A2, A3 and stack
3605// f32 - Only passed in f32 registers if no int reg has been used yet to hold
3606// an argument. Otherwise, passed in A1, A2, A3 and stack.
3607// f64 - Only passed in two aliased f32 registers if no int reg has been used
3608// yet to hold an argument. Otherwise, use A2, A3 and stack. If A1 is
3609// not used, it must be shadowed. If only A3 is available, shadow it and
3610// go to stack.
3611// vXiX - Received as scalarized i32s, passed in A0 - A3 and the stack.
3612// vXf32 - Passed in either a pair of registers {A0, A1}, {A2, A3} or {A0 - A3}
3613// with the remainder spilled to the stack.
3614// vXf64 - Passed in either {A0, A1, A2, A3} or {A2, A3} and in both cases
3615// spilling the remainder to the stack.
3616//
3617// For vararg functions, all arguments are passed in A0, A1, A2, A3 and stack.
3618//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3619
3620static bool CC_MipsO32(unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT,
3621 CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo, ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags,
3622 CCState &State, ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> F64Regs) {
3623 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget = static_cast<const MipsSubtarget &>(
3624 State.getMachineFunction().getSubtarget());
3625
3626 static const MCPhysReg IntRegs[] = { Mips::A0, Mips::A1, Mips::A2, Mips::A3 };
3627
3628 const MipsCCState * MipsState = static_cast<MipsCCState *>(&State);
3629
3630 static const MCPhysReg F32Regs[] = { Mips::F12, Mips::F14 };
3631
3632 static const MCPhysReg FloatVectorIntRegs[] = { Mips::A0, Mips::A2 };
3633
3634 // Do not process byval args here.
3635 if (ArgFlags.isByVal())
3636 return true;
3637
3638 // Promote i8 and i16
3639 if (ArgFlags.isInReg() && !Subtarget.isLittle()) {
3640 if (LocVT == MVT::i8 || LocVT == MVT::i16 || LocVT == MVT::i32) {
3641 LocVT = MVT::i32;
3642 if (ArgFlags.isSExt())
3643 LocInfo = CCValAssign::SExtUpper;
3644 else if (ArgFlags.isZExt())
3645 LocInfo = CCValAssign::ZExtUpper;
3646 else
3647 LocInfo = CCValAssign::AExtUpper;
3648 }
3649 }
3650
3651 // Promote i8 and i16
3652 if (LocVT == MVT::i8 || LocVT == MVT::i16) {
3653 LocVT = MVT::i32;
3654 if (ArgFlags.isSExt())
3655 LocInfo = CCValAssign::SExt;
3656 else if (ArgFlags.isZExt())
3657 LocInfo = CCValAssign::ZExt;
3658 else
3659 LocInfo = CCValAssign::AExt;
3660 }
3661
3662 unsigned Reg;
3663
3664 // f32 and f64 are allocated in A0, A1, A2, A3 when either of the following
3665 // is true: function is vararg, argument is 3rd or higher, there is previous
3666 // argument which is not f32 or f64.
3667 bool AllocateFloatsInIntReg = State.isVarArg() || ValNo > 1 ||
3668 State.getFirstUnallocated(F32Regs) != ValNo;
3669 unsigned OrigAlign = ArgFlags.getOrigAlign();
3670 bool isI64 = (ValVT == MVT::i32 && OrigAlign == 8);
3671 bool isVectorFloat = MipsState->WasOriginalArgVectorFloat(ValNo);
3672
3673 // The MIPS vector ABI for floats passes them in a pair of registers
3674 if (ValVT == MVT::i32 && isVectorFloat) {
3675 // This is the start of an vector that was scalarized into an unknown number
3676 // of components. It doesn't matter how many there are. Allocate one of the
3677 // notional 8 byte aligned registers which map onto the argument stack, and
3678 // shadow the register lost to alignment requirements.
3679 if (ArgFlags.isSplit()) {
3680 Reg = State.AllocateReg(FloatVectorIntRegs);
3681 if (Reg == Mips::A2)
3682 State.AllocateReg(Mips::A1);
3683 else if (Reg == 0)
3684 State.AllocateReg(Mips::A3);
3685 } else {
3686 // If we're an intermediate component of the split, we can just attempt to
3687 // allocate a register directly.
3688 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3689 }
3690 } else if (ValVT == MVT::i32 || (ValVT == MVT::f32 && AllocateFloatsInIntReg)) {
3691 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3692 // If this is the first part of an i64 arg,
3693 // the allocated register must be either A0 or A2.
3694 if (isI64 && (Reg == Mips::A1 || Reg == Mips::A3))
3695 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3696 LocVT = MVT::i32;
3697 } else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && AllocateFloatsInIntReg) {
3698 // Allocate int register and shadow next int register. If first
3699 // available register is Mips::A1 or Mips::A3, shadow it too.
3700 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3701 if (Reg == Mips::A1 || Reg == Mips::A3)
3702 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3703 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3704 LocVT = MVT::i32;
3705 } else if (ValVT.isFloatingPoint() && !AllocateFloatsInIntReg) {
3706 // we are guaranteed to find an available float register
3707 if (ValVT == MVT::f32) {
3708 Reg = State.AllocateReg(F32Regs);
3709 // Shadow int register
3710 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3711 } else {
3712 Reg = State.AllocateReg(F64Regs);
3713 // Shadow int registers
3714 unsigned Reg2 = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3715 if (Reg2 == Mips::A1 || Reg2 == Mips::A3)
3716 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3717 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs);
3718 }
3719 } else
3720 llvm_unreachable("Cannot handle this ValVT.");
3721
3722 if (!Reg) {
3723 unsigned Offset = State.AllocateStack(ValVT.getStoreSize(), OrigAlign);
3724 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset, LocVT, LocInfo));
3725 } else
3726 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
3727
3728 return false;
3729}

3770SDValue MipsTargetLowering::passArgOnStack(SDValue StackPtr, unsigned Offset,
3771 SDValue Chain, SDValue Arg,
3772 const SDLoc &DL, bool IsTailCall,
3773 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3774 if (!IsTailCall) {
3775 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, StackPtr, Offset);
3776 return DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Arg, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo());

3784 /* Alignment = */ 0, MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile);
