3786
3787void MipsTargetLowering::
3788getOpndList(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Ops,
3789 std::deque<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>> &RegsToPass,
3790 bool IsPICCall, bool GlobalOrExternal, bool InternalLinkage,
3791 bool IsCallReloc, CallLoweringInfo &CLI, SDValue Callee,
3792 SDValue Chain) const {
3793 // Insert node "GP copy globalreg" before call to function.
3794 //
3795 // R_MIPS_CALL* operators (emitted when non-internal functions are called
3796 // in PIC mode) allow symbols to be resolved via lazy binding.
3797 // The lazy binding stub requires GP to point to the GOT.
3798 // Note that we don't need GP to point to the GOT for indirect calls
3799 // (when R_MIPS_CALL* is not used for the call) because Mips linker generates
3800 // lazy binding stub for a function only when R_MIPS_CALL* are the only relocs
3801 // used for the function (that is, Mips linker doesn't generate lazy binding
3802 // stub for a function whose address is taken in the program).
3803 //
3804 // When using the capability table we don't need $GP, but use $cgp instead.
3805 //
3806 if (IsPICCall && !InternalLinkage && IsCallReloc && !ABI.UsesCapabilityTable()) {
3807 unsigned GPReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::GP_64 : Mips::GP;
3808 EVT Ty = ABI.IsN64() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
3809 RegsToPass.push_back(
3810 std::make_pair(GPReg, getGlobalReg(CLI.DAG, Ty, /*IsForTls=*/false)));
3811 }
3812
3813 // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes chained together with token
3814 // chain and flag operands which copy the outgoing args into registers.
3815 // The InFlag in necessary since all emitted instructions must be
3816 // stuck together.
3817 SDValue InFlag;
3818
3819 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3820 Chain = CLI.DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, CLI.DL, RegsToPass[i].first,
3821 RegsToPass[i].second, InFlag);
3822 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
3823 }
3824
3825 // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are
3826 // known live into the call.
3827 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i)
3828 Ops.push_back(CLI.DAG.getRegister(RegsToPass[i].first,
3829 RegsToPass[i].second.getValueType()));
3830
3831 // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
3832 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
3833 const uint32_t *Mask =
3834 TRI->getCallPreservedMask(CLI.DAG.getMachineFunction(), CLI.CallConv);
3835 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
3836 if (Subtarget.inMips16HardFloat()) {
3837 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(CLI.Callee)) {
3838 StringRef Sym = G->getGlobal()->getName();
3839 Function *F = G->getGlobal()->getParent()->getFunction(Sym);
3840 if (F && F->hasFnAttribute("__Mips16RetHelper")) {
3841 Mask = MipsRegisterInfo::getMips16RetHelperMask();
3842 }
3843 }
3844 }
3845 Ops.push_back(CLI.DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
3846
3847 if (InFlag.getNode())
3848 Ops.push_back(InFlag);
3849}
3850
3851void MipsTargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
3852 SDNode *Node) const {
3853 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
3854 default:
3855 return;
3856 case Mips::JALR:
3857 case Mips::JALRPseudo:
3858 case Mips::JALR64:
3859 case Mips::JALR64Pseudo:
3860 case Mips::JALR16_MM:
3861 case Mips::JALRC16_MMR6:
3862 case Mips::TAILCALLREG:
3863 case Mips::TAILCALLREG64:
3864 case Mips::TAILCALLR6REG:
3865 case Mips::TAILCALL64R6REG:
3866 case Mips::TAILCALLREG_MM:
3867 case Mips::TAILCALLREG_MMR6: {
3868 if (!EmitJalrReloc ||
3869 Subtarget.inMips16Mode() ||
3870 !isPositionIndependent() ||
3871 Node->getNumOperands() < 1 ||
3872 Node->getOperand(0).getNumOperands() < 2) {
3873 return;
3874 }
3875 // We are after the callee address, set by LowerCall().
3876 // If added to MI, asm printer will emit .reloc R_MIPS_JALR for the
3877 // symbol.
3878 const SDValue TargetAddr = Node->getOperand(0).getOperand(1);
3879 StringRef Sym;
3880 if (const GlobalAddressSDNode *G =
3881 dyn_cast_or_null<const GlobalAddressSDNode>(TargetAddr)) {
3882 Sym = G->getGlobal()->getName();
3883 }
3884 else if (const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES =
3885 dyn_cast_or_null<const ExternalSymbolSDNode>(TargetAddr)) {
3886 Sym = ES->getSymbol();
3887 }
3888
3889 if (Sym.empty())
3890 return;
3891
3892 MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
3893 MCSymbol *S = MF->getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Sym);
3894 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateMCSymbol(S, MipsII::MO_JALR));
3895 }
3896 }
3897}
3898
3899/// LowerCall - functions arguments are copied from virtual regs to
3900/// (physical regs)/(stack frame), CALLSEQ_START and CALLSEQ_END are emitted.
3901SDValue
3902MipsTargetLowering::LowerCall(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
3903 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
3904 SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
3905 SDLoc DL = CLI.DL;
3906 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
3907 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
3908 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
3909 SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
3910 SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
3911 bool &IsTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall;
3912 CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
3913 bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
3914
3915 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
3916 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
3917 const TargetFrameLowering *TFL = Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
3918 MipsFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
3919 bool IsPIC = isPositionIndependent();
3920
3921 // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
3922 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
3923 MipsCCState CCInfo(
3924 CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext(),
3925 MipsCCState::getSpecialCallingConvForCallee(Callee.getNode(), Subtarget));
3926
3927 const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES =
3928 dyn_cast_or_null<const ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee.getNode());
3929
3930 // There is one case where CALLSEQ_START..CALLSEQ_END can be nested, which
3931 // is during the lowering of a call with a byval argument which produces
3932 // a call to memcpy. For the O32 case, this causes the caller to allocate
3933 // stack space for the reserved argument area for the callee, then recursively
3934 // again for the memcpy call. In the NEWABI case, this doesn't occur as those
3935 // ABIs mandate that the callee allocates the reserved argument area. We do
3936 // still produce nested CALLSEQ_START..CALLSEQ_END with zero space though.
3937 //
3938 // If the callee has a byval argument and memcpy is used, we are mandated
3939 // to already have produced a reserved argument area for the callee for O32.
3940 // Therefore, the reserved argument area can be reused for both calls.
3941 //
3942 // Other cases of calling memcpy cannot have a chain with a CALLSEQ_START
3943 // present, as we have yet to hook that node onto the chain.
3944 //
3945 // Hence, the CALLSEQ_START and CALLSEQ_END nodes can be eliminated in this
3946 // case. GCC does a similar trick, in that wherever possible, it calculates
3947 // the maximum out going argument area (including the reserved area), and
3948 // preallocates the stack space on entrance to the caller.
3949 //
3950 // FIXME: We should do the same for efficiency and space.
3951
3952 // Note: The check on the calling convention below must match
3953 // MipsABIInfo::GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes().
3954 bool MemcpyInByVal = ES &&
3955 StringRef(ES->getSymbol()) == StringRef("memcpy") &&
3956 CallConv != CallingConv::Fast &&
3957 Chain.getOpcode() == ISD::CALLSEQ_START;
3958
3959 // Allocate the reserved argument area. It seems strange to do this from the
3960 // caller side but removing it breaks the frame size calculation.
3961 unsigned ReservedArgArea =
3962 MemcpyInByVal ? 0 : ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(CallConv);
3963 CCInfo.AllocateStack(ReservedArgArea, 1);
3964
3965 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_Mips, CLI.getArgs(),
3966 ES ? ES->getSymbol() : nullptr);
3967
3968 // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack.
3969 unsigned NextStackOffset = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
3970
3971 // Check if it's really possible to do a tail call. Restrict it to functions
3972 // that are part of this compilation unit.
3973 bool InternalLinkage = false;
3974 if (IsTailCall) {
3975 IsTailCall = isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
3976 CCInfo, NextStackOffset, *MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>());
3977 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
3978 InternalLinkage = G->getGlobal()->hasInternalLinkage();
3979 IsTailCall &= (InternalLinkage || G->getGlobal()->hasLocalLinkage() ||
3980 G->getGlobal()->hasPrivateLinkage() ||
3981 G->getGlobal()->hasHiddenVisibility() ||
3982 G->getGlobal()->hasProtectedVisibility());
3983 }
3984 }
3985 if (!IsTailCall && CLI.CS && CLI.CS.isMustTailCall())
3986 report_fatal_error("failed to perform tail call elimination on a call "
3987 "site marked musttail");
3988
3989 if (IsTailCall)
3990 ++NumTailCalls;
3991
3992 // Chain is the output chain of the last Load/Store or CopyToReg node.
3993 // ByValChain is the output chain of the last Memcpy node created for copying
3994 // byval arguments to the stack.
3995 unsigned StackAlignment = TFL->getStackAlignment();
3996 NextStackOffset = alignTo(NextStackOffset, StackAlignment);
3997 SDValue NextStackOffsetVal = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(NextStackOffset, DL, true);
3998
3999 if (!(IsTailCall || MemcpyInByVal))
4000 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, NextStackOffset, 0, DL);
4001
4002 SDValue StackPtr =
4003 DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, ABI.GetStackPtr(),
4004 getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
4005 ABI.StackAddrSpace()));
4006
4007 std::deque<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>> RegsToPass;
4008 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
4009
4010 CCInfo.rewindByValRegsInfo();
4011
4012 unsigned CapArgs = 0;
4013 unsigned IntArgs = 0;
4014 int FirstOffset = -1;
4015 int LastOffset;
4016
4017 // Walk the register/memloc assignments, inserting copies/loads.
4018 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4019 SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
4020 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
4021 MVT ValVT = VA.getValVT(), LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
4022 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
4023 bool UseUpperBits = false;
4024
4025 // ByVal Arg.
4026 if (Flags.isByVal()) {
4027 unsigned FirstByValReg, LastByValReg;
4028 unsigned ByValIdx = CCInfo.getInRegsParamsProcessed();
4029 CCInfo.getInRegsParamInfo(ByValIdx, FirstByValReg, LastByValReg);
4030
4031 assert(Flags.getByValSize() &&
4032 "ByVal args of size 0 should have been ignored by front-end.");
4033 assert(ByValIdx < CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount());
4034 assert(!IsTailCall &&
4035 "Do not tail-call optimize if there is a byval argument.");
4036 passByValArg(Chain, DL, RegsToPass, MemOpChains, StackPtr, MFI, DAG, Arg,
4037 FirstByValReg, LastByValReg, Flags, Subtarget.isLittle(),
4038 VA);
4039 CCInfo.nextInRegsParam();
4040 continue;
4041 }
4042
4043 // Promote the value if needed.
4044 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
4045 default:
4046 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
4047 case CCValAssign::Full:
4048 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
4049 if ((ValVT == MVT::f32 && LocVT == MVT::i32) ||
4050 (ValVT == MVT::f64 && LocVT == MVT::i64) ||
4051 (ValVT == MVT::i64 && LocVT == MVT::f64))
4052 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Arg);
4053 else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && LocVT == MVT::i32) {
4054 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
4055 Arg, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
4056 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
4057 Arg, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
4058 if (!Subtarget.isLittle())
4059 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
4060 unsigned LocRegLo = VA.getLocReg();
4061 unsigned LocRegHigh = getNextIntArgReg(LocRegLo);
4062 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(LocRegLo, Lo));
4063 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(LocRegHigh, Hi));
4064 continue;
4065 }
4066 }
4067 break;
4068 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
4069 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Arg);
4070 break;
4071 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper:
4072 UseUpperBits = true;
4073 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4074 case CCValAssign::SExt:
4075 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg);
4076 break;
4077 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper:
4078 UseUpperBits = true;
4079 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4080 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
4081 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg);
4082 break;
4083 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper:
4084 UseUpperBits = true;
4085 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4086 case CCValAssign::AExt:
4087 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg);
4088 break;
4089 }
4090
4091 if (UseUpperBits) {
4092 unsigned ValSizeInBits = Outs[i].ArgVT.getSizeInBits();
4093 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits();
4094 Arg = DAG.getNode(
4095 ISD::SHL, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg,
4096 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT()));
4097 }
4098
4099 // Arguments that can be passed on register must be kept at
4100 // RegsToPass vector
4101 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
4102 if (ValVT.isFatPointer())
4103 CapArgs++;
4104 else if ((VA.getLocReg() >= Mips::A0_64) &&
4105 (VA.getLocReg() <= Mips::T3_64))
4106 IntArgs++;
4107 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg));
4108 continue;
4109 }
4110
4111 // Register can't get to this point...
4112 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
4113
4114 // Ignore leading undef args (inserted by clang for alignment), as they
4115 // break varargs
4116 if (FirstOffset == -1 && Arg.isUndef() && ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
4117 continue;
4118
4119 if (FirstOffset == -1)
4120 FirstOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset();
4121 LastOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset() + (Arg.getValueSizeInBits() / 8);
4122 // emit ISD::STORE whichs stores the
4123 // parameter value to a stack Location
4124 MemOpChains.push_back(passArgOnStack(StackPtr, VA.getLocMemOffset(),
4125 Chain, Arg, DL, IsTailCall, DAG));
4126 }
4127 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
4128 if (FirstOffset != -1) {
4129 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, StackPtr, FirstOffset);
4130 PtrOff = setBounds(DAG, PtrOff, LastOffset, /*CSetBoundsStatsLogged=*/true);
4131 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, CapType,
4132 DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_perms_and, DL, MVT::i64), PtrOff,
4133 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0xFFD7, DL));
4134 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(Mips::C13, PtrOff));
4135 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats) {
4136 StringRef Name = "<unknown function>";
4137 if (ES) {
4138 Name = ES->getSymbol();
4139 } else if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
4140 Name = G->getGlobal()->getName();
4141 }
4142 cheri::CSetBoundsStats->add(
4143 1, LastOffset, "variadic call lowering",
4144 cheri::SetBoundsPointerSource::Stack,
4145 StringRef("setting varargs bounds for call to ") + Name,
4146 cheri::inferSourceLocation(DL.getDebugLoc(),
4147 DAG.getMachineFunction().getName()));
4148 }
4149 } else {
4150 bool ShouldClearC13 = false;
4151 // We only need to clear $c13 (for on-stack arguments if the calling
4152 // function had args on the stack (i.e. $c13 was a live in)
4153 // However, $c13 being a live in is only set once lowerVASTART is processed
4154 // so we just look if the current function is variadic in the IR Decl
4155 // TODO: should we just mark c13 as live-in in for all variadic functions
4156 // in MipsTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments()?
4157 if (MF.getFunction().isVarArg())
4158 ShouldClearC13 = true;
4159 // Also clear $c13 if it was marked as live-in due to having
4160 if (MF.getRegInfo().isLiveIn(Mips::C13))
4161 ShouldClearC13 = true;
4162 if (ShouldClearC13) {
4163 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Clearing $c13 in " << MF.getName()
4164 << "(is varargs: " << MF.getFunction().isVarArg()
4165 << ") callee = ");
4166 LLVM_DEBUG(Callee.dump(&DAG););
4167 }
4168 // We always clear $c13 if we are compiling at -O0 or -O1 since this helps
4169 // us catch errors with calling convention mismatches.
4170 if (getTargetMachine().getOptLevel() < CodeGenOpt::Default)
4171 ShouldClearC13 = true;
4172 if (ShouldClearC13)
4173 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(Mips::C13, DAG.getNullCapability(DL, CapType)));
4174 }
4175 }
4176 // If we're doing a CCall then any unused arg registers should be zero.
4177 if (!UseClearRegs && (CallConv == CallingConv::CHERI_CCall)) {
4178 assert(CapArgs >= 2);
4179 CapArgs -= 2;
4180 // Optional argument registers for CCall calling convention
4181 static const unsigned RegList[] = { Mips::C3, Mips::C4, Mips::C5, Mips::C6,
4182 Mips::C7, Mips::C8, Mips::C9, Mips::C10 };
4183 for (unsigned i=CapArgs ; i<8 ; i++) {
4184 SDValue Zero = DAG.getNullCapability(DL, CapType);
4185 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(RegList[i], Zero));
4186 }
4187 static const unsigned IntRegList[] = { Mips::A0_64, Mips::A1_64,
4188 Mips::A2_64, Mips::A3_64, Mips::T0_64, Mips::T1_64, Mips::T2_64,
4189 Mips::T3_64 };
4190 for (unsigned i=IntArgs ; i<8 ; i++) {
4191 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64);
4192 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(IntRegList[i], Zero));
4193 }
4194 }
4195
4196 // Transform all store nodes into one single node because all store
4197 // nodes are independent of each other.
4198 if (!MemOpChains.empty())
4199 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
4200
4201 // If the callee is a GlobalAddress/ExternalSymbol node (quite common, every
4202 // direct call is) turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress/TargetExternalSymbol
4203 // node so that legalize doesn't hack it.
4204
4205 EVT Ty = Callee.getValueType();
4206 bool GlobalOrExternal = false, IsCallReloc = false;
4207
4208 const bool CheriCapTable = Subtarget.useCheriCapTable();
4209 // In the legacy ABI we want to load only the vaddr and the use cgetpccsetoffset
4210 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap() && !CheriCapTable)
4211 Ty = MVT::i64;
4212
4213 // The long-calls feature is ignored in case of PIC.
4214 // While we do not support -mshared / -mno-shared properly,
4215 // ignore long-calls in case of -mabicalls too.
4216 if (!Subtarget.isABICalls() && !IsPIC) {
4217 // If the function should be called using "long call",
4218 // get its address into a register to prevent using
4219 // of the `jal` instruction for the direct call.
4220 if (auto *N = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
4221 if (Subtarget.useLongCalls())
4222 Callee = Subtarget.hasSym32()
4223 ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
4224 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
4225 } else if (auto *N = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
4226 bool UseLongCalls = Subtarget.useLongCalls();
4227 // If the function has long-call/far/near attribute
4228 // it overrides command line switch pased to the backend.
4229 if (auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(N->getGlobal())) {
4230 if (F->hasFnAttribute("long-call"))
4231 UseLongCalls = true;
4232 else if (F->hasFnAttribute("short-call"))
4233 UseLongCalls = false;
4234 }
4235 if (UseLongCalls)
4236 Callee = Subtarget.hasSym32()
4237 ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG)
4238 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG);
4239 }
4240 }
4241
4242 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
4243 const GlobalValue *GV = G->getGlobal();
4244 if (CheriCapTable) {
4245 Callee = getCallTargetFromCapTable(G, DL, CapType, DAG, Chain,
4246 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(GV));
4247 IsCallReloc = true;
4248 } else if (IsPIC || ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
4249 // Legacy ABI also needs to load from GOT in non-PIC since otherwise
4250 // it will attempt to use a JAL relocation in a CGetPCCSetOffset (and
4251 // corrupt the instruction)
4252 InternalLinkage = GV->hasInternalLinkage();
4253
4254 if (LargeGOT) {
4255 Callee = getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(G, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_CALL_HI16,
4256 MipsII::MO_CALL_LO16, Chain,
4257 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(GV), GV->isThreadLocal());
4258 IsCallReloc = true;
4259 } else if (InternalLinkage)
4260 Callee = getAddrLocal(G, DL, Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64(), GV->isThreadLocal());
4261 else {
4262 Callee = getAddrGlobal(G, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_CALL, Chain,
4263 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(GV), GV->isThreadLocal());
4264 IsCallReloc = true;
4265 }
4266 } else {
4267 assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
4268 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(
4269 GV, DL, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), 0), 0, MipsII::MO_NO_FLAG);
4270 }
4271 GlobalOrExternal = true;
4272 }
4273 else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
4274 const char *Sym = S->getSymbol();
4275
4276 if (CheriCapTable) {
4277 Callee = getCallTargetFromCapTable(S, DL, CapType, DAG, Chain,
4278 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(Sym));
4279 IsCallReloc = true;
4280 } else if (!IsPIC) { // static
4281 assert(!ABI.UsesCapabilityTable());
4282 // NOTE: address space zero is correct here since we are in the legacy ABI
4283 Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(
4284 Sym, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), 0), MipsII::MO_NO_FLAG);
4285 } else if (LargeGOT) {
4286 Callee = getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(S, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_CALL_HI16,
4287 MipsII::MO_CALL_LO16, Chain,
4288 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(Sym), /*IsForTls=*/false);
4289 IsCallReloc = true;
4290 } else { // PIC
4291 Callee = getAddrGlobal(S, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_CALL, Chain,
4292 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(Sym), /*IsForTls=*/false);
4293 IsCallReloc = true;
4294 }
4295
4296 GlobalOrExternal = true;
4297 }
4298 if (CheriCapTable && !GlobalOrExternal) {
4299 // XXXAR: FIXME: calling function pointers may require some more changes for
4300 // shared libs!
4301 }
4302 // If we're in the sandbox ABI, then we need to turn the address into a
4303 // PCC-derived capability.
4304 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap() && (!Callee.getValueType().isFatPointer())) {
4305 if (CheriCapTable)
4306 llvm_unreachable("Should not derive address from PCC with cap table");
4307 Callee = setPccOffset(DAG, DL, Callee);
4308 }
4309
4310
4311 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops(1, Chain);
4312 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
4313
4314 getOpndList(Ops, RegsToPass, IsPIC, GlobalOrExternal, InternalLinkage,
4315 IsCallReloc, CLI, Callee, Chain);
4316
4317 // If we're doing a CCall then any unused arg registers should be zero.
4318 if (UseClearRegs && (CallConv == CallingConv::CHERI_CCall)) {
4319 assert(CapArgs >= 2);
4320 uint32_t ClearRegsMask = 0;
4321 // Cap registers C1-C10 are used for arguments (C1/C2 for the CHERI object)
4322 for (unsigned i=CapArgs+1 ; i<11 ; i++) {
4323 ClearRegsMask |= 1 << i;
4324 }
4325 assert(ClearRegsMask <= 0xffff);
4326 ClearRegsMask <<= 16;
4327 // Int registers $4-$11 are used for arguments and v0 ($1) for the method
4328 // number
4329 for (unsigned i=IntArgs+4 ; i<12 ; i++) {
4330 ClearRegsMask |= 1 << i;
4331 assert((1 << i) <= 0xffff);
4332 }
4333 Ops.insert(Ops.begin()+2, DAG.getConstant(ClearRegsMask, DL, MVT::i32));
4334 Chain = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CheriJmpLink, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
4335 } else {
4336 if (IsTailCall) {
4337 MF.getFrameInfo().setHasTailCall();
4338 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TailCall, DL, MVT::Other, Ops);
4339 }
4340
4341 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
4342 Chain = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapJmpLink, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
4343 else
4344 Chain = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::JmpLink, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
4345 }
4346 SDValue InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
4347
4348 // Create the CALLSEQ_END node in the case of where it is not a call to
4349 // memcpy.
4350 if (!(MemcpyInByVal)) {
4351 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, NextStackOffsetVal,
4352 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL, true), InFlag, DL);
4353 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
4354 }
4355
4356 // Handle result values, copying them out of physregs into vregs that we
4357 // return.
4358 return LowerCallResult(Chain, InFlag, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins, DL, DAG,
4359 InVals, CLI);
4360}
4361
4362SDValue MipsTargetLowering::setPccOffset(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc DL,
4363 SDValue Offset) const {
4364 auto GetPCC = DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_pcc_get, DL, MVT::i64);
4365 auto SetOffset =
4366 DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_set, DL, MVT::i64);
4367 auto PCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, CapType, GetPCC);
4368 return DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, CapType, SetOffset, PCC,
4369 Offset);
4370}

4372SDValue MipsTargetLowering::cFromDDC(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc DL,
4373 SDValue Offset) const {
4374 auto CFromDDC = DAG.getConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_from_ddc, DL, MVT::i64);
4375 return DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, CapType, CFromDDC, Offset);
4376}
4377
4378/// LowerCallResult - Lower the result values of a call into the
4379/// appropriate copies out of appropriate physical registers.
4380SDValue MipsTargetLowering::LowerCallResult(
4381 SDValue Chain, SDValue InFlag, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
4382 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
4383 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals,
4384 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI) const {
4385 // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
4386 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
4387 MipsCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
4388 *DAG.getContext());
4389
4390 const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES =
4391 dyn_cast_or_null<const ExternalSymbolSDNode>(CLI.Callee.getNode());
4392 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_Mips, CLI.RetTy,
4393 ES ? ES->getSymbol() : nullptr);
4394
4395
4396 // Calling an external function could change the value of $cgp. We need to
4397 // restore it to the $cgp on entry before calling the next function.
4398 // In the PLT ABI we must restore the old value of $cgp prior to return if
4399 // we called an external function or a function pointer since these may have
4400 // changed the $cgp value. This ensures that the callee still has the correct
4401 // value for $cgp after calling any local function (even if that function
4402 // calls an external function).
4403 // This could cause errors in the following sequence of calls:
4404 //
4405 // func_in_dso1() calls func_in_dso2() -> on return $cgp is set to the $cgp of
4406 // DSO2. If func_in_dso1() then calls another function in DSO1 (i.e. any call
4407 // without a trampoline that changes $cgp) that function will still have the
4408 // $cgp of DSO2 and will crash (or load the wrong globals).
4409 //
4410 // Note: we do not need to do this for the pc-relative ABI since each function
4411 // derives the value of $cgp from the $pcc on entry ($c12)
4412 //
4413 // TODO: This could be optimized to only be done prior to the next call or
4414 // return, but I think this will only remove very few instructions
4415 // E.g. we can omit the restore in the case where we call a function pointer
4416 // next since that will not use $cgp
4417 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable() && MCTargetOptions::cheriCapabilityTableABI() !=
4418 CheriCapabilityTableABI::Pcrel) {
4419 bool LocalCallOptimization = false;
4420 bool IsPerFileOrPerFunctionCapTable = false; // TODO: add option
4421 // FIXME: for captable per file/function this should always be false!
4422 // For now we just require -O0 for per-file/per-function captable
4423 // When optimization is enabled, we can omit the restoring of $cgp
4424 if (!IsPerFileOrPerFunctionCapTable && !isOptNone(DAG.getMachineFunction())) {
4425 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(CLI.Callee)) {
4426 LocalCallOptimization = G->getGlobal()->isDSOLocal();
4427 }
4428 }
4429
4430 if (!LocalCallOptimization) {
4431 // Note: we don't need to restore the entry $cgp when calling a DSO local
4432 // function since all local functions ensure that $cgp on entry == $cgp on exit
4433 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, ABI.GetGlobalCapability(), getCapGlobalReg(CLI.DAG, CapType), InFlag);
4434 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
4435 } else {
4436 // TODO: at -O1 assert that $cgp before and after is the same?
4437#if 0
4438 SDNode *Equal = DAG.getMachineNode(Mips::CEXEQ32, DL, MVT::i32,
4439 DAG.getRegister(ABI.GetGlobalCapability(), CapType), getCapGlobalReg(CLI.DAG, CapType));
4440 SDNode *TrapNotEqual = DAG.getMachineNode(Mips::TEQ, DL, MVT::Other, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32, true), SDValue(Equal, 0), DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32, true));
4441 // FIXME: how to add this to chain correctly?
4442 DAG.dump();
4443#endif
4444 }
4445 }
4446
4447 // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
4448 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
4449 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
4450 assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
4451
4452 SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RVLocs[i].getLocReg(),
4453 RVLocs[i].getLocVT(), InFlag);
4454 Chain = Val.getValue(1);
4455 InFlag = Val.getValue(2);
4456
4457 if (VA.isUpperBitsInLoc()) {
4458 unsigned ValSizeInBits = Ins[i].ArgVT.getSizeInBits();
4459 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits();
4460 unsigned Shift =
4461 VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExtUpper ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SRA;
4462 Val = DAG.getNode(
4463 Shift, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val,
4464 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT()));
4465 }
4466
4467 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
4468 default:
4469 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
4470 case CCValAssign::Full:
4471 break;
4472 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
4473 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
4474 break;
4475 case CCValAssign::AExt:
4476 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper:
4477 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
4478 break;
4479 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
4480 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper:
4481 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val,
4482 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
4483 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
4484 break;
4485 case CCValAssign::SExt:
4486 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper:
4487 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val,
4488 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
4489 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
4490 break;
4491 }
4492
4493 InVals.push_back(Val);
4494 }
4495
4496 return Chain;
4497}
4498
4499static SDValue UnpackFromArgumentSlot(SDValue Val, const CCValAssign &VA,
4500 EVT ArgVT, const SDLoc &DL,
4501 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
4502 MVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
4503 EVT ValVT = VA.getValVT();
4504
4505 // Shift into the upper bits if necessary.
4506 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
4507 default:
4508 break;
4509 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper:
4510 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper:
4511 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper: {
4512 unsigned ValSizeInBits = ArgVT.getSizeInBits();
4513 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits();
4514 unsigned Opcode =
4515 VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExtUpper ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SRA;
4516 Val = DAG.getNode(
4517 Opcode, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val,
4518 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT()));
4519 break;
4520 }
4521 }
4522
4523 // If this is an value smaller than the argument slot size (32-bit for O32,
4524 // 64-bit for N32/N64), it has been promoted in some way to the argument slot
4525 // size. Extract the value and insert any appropriate assertions regarding
4526 // sign/zero extension.
4527 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
4528 default:
4529 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
4530 case CCValAssign::Full:
4531 break;
4532 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper:
4533 case CCValAssign::AExt:
4534 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ValVT, Val);
4535 break;
4536 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper:
4537 case CCValAssign::SExt:
4538 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, DL, LocVT, Val, DAG.getValueType(ValVT));
4539 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ValVT, Val);
4540 break;
4541 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper:
4542 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
4543 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, LocVT, Val, DAG.getValueType(ValVT));
4544 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ValVT, Val);
4545 break;
4546 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
4547 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ValVT, Val);
4548 break;
4549 }
4550
4551 return Val;
4552}
4553
4554//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4555// Formal Arguments Calling Convention Implementation
4556//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4557/// LowerFormalArguments - transform physical registers into virtual registers
4558/// and generate load operations for arguments places on the stack.
4559SDValue MipsTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
4560 SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
4561 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
4562 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
4563 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4564 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
4565 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
4566
4567 MipsFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(0);
4568
4569 // Used with vargs to acumulate store chains.
4570 std::vector<SDValue> OutChains;
4571
4572 // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
4573 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
4574 MipsCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs,
4575 *DAG.getContext());
4576 CCInfo.AllocateStack(ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(CallConv), 1);
4577 const Function &Func = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
4578 Function::const_arg_iterator FuncArg = Func.arg_begin();
4579
4580 if (Func.hasFnAttribute("interrupt") && !Func.arg_empty())
4581 report_fatal_error(
4582 "Functions with the interrupt attribute cannot have arguments!");
4583
4584 CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_Mips_FixedArg);
4585 MipsFI->setFormalArgInfo(CCInfo.getNextStackOffset(),
4586 CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount() > 0);
4587
4588 unsigned CurArgIdx = 0;
4589 CCInfo.rewindByValRegsInfo();
4590 unsigned CapArgReg = -1U;
4591
4592 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4593 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
4594 if (Ins[i].isOrigArg()) {
4595 std::advance(FuncArg, Ins[i].getOrigArgIndex() - CurArgIdx);
4596 CurArgIdx = Ins[i].getOrigArgIndex();
4597 }
4598 EVT ValVT = VA.getValVT();
4599 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Ins[i].Flags;
4600 bool IsRegLoc = VA.isRegLoc();
4601
4602 if (Flags.isByVal()) {
4603 assert(Ins[i].isOrigArg() && "Byval arguments cannot be implicit");
4604 unsigned FirstByValReg, LastByValReg;
4605 unsigned ByValIdx = CCInfo.getInRegsParamsProcessed();
4606 CCInfo.getInRegsParamInfo(ByValIdx, FirstByValReg, LastByValReg);
4607
4608 assert(Flags.getByValSize() &&
4609 "ByVal args of size 0 should have been ignored by front-end.");
4610 assert(ByValIdx < CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount());
4611 copyByValRegs(Chain, DL, OutChains, DAG, Flags, InVals, &*FuncArg,
4612 FirstByValReg, LastByValReg, VA, CCInfo);
4613 CCInfo.nextInRegsParam();
4614 continue;
4615 }
4616
4617 // Arguments stored on registers
4618 if (IsRegLoc) {
4619 MVT RegVT = VA.getLocVT();
4620 unsigned ArgReg = VA.getLocReg();
4621 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegVT);
4622
4623 // Transform the arguments stored on
4624 // physical registers into virtual ones
4625 unsigned Reg = addLiveIn(DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgReg, RC);
4626 SDValue ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, RegVT);
4627
4628 ArgValue = UnpackFromArgumentSlot(ArgValue, VA, Ins[i].ArgVT, DL, DAG);
4629
4630 // Handle floating point arguments passed in integer registers and
4631 // long double arguments passed in floating point registers.
4632 if ((RegVT == MVT::i32 && ValVT == MVT::f32) ||
4633 (RegVT == MVT::i64 && ValVT == MVT::f64) ||
4634 (RegVT == MVT::f64 && ValVT == MVT::i64))
4635 ArgValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ValVT, ArgValue);
4636 else if (ABI.IsO32() && RegVT == MVT::i32 &&
4637 ValVT == MVT::f64) {
4638 unsigned Reg2 = addLiveIn(DAG.getMachineFunction(),
4639 getNextIntArgReg(ArgReg), RC);
4640 SDValue ArgValue2 = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg2, RegVT);
4641 if (!Subtarget.isLittle())
4642 std::swap(ArgValue, ArgValue2);
4643 ArgValue = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64,
4644 ArgValue, ArgValue2);
4645 }
4646
4647 InVals.push_back(ArgValue);
4648 } else { // VA.isRegLoc()
4649 MVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
4650
4651 if (ABI.IsO32()) {
4652 // We ought to be able to use LocVT directly but O32 sets it to i32
4653 // when allocating floating point values to integer registers.
4654 // This shouldn't influence how we load the value into registers unless
4655 // we are targeting softfloat.
4656 if (VA.getValVT().isFloatingPoint() && !Subtarget.useSoftFloat())
4657 LocVT = VA.getValVT();
4658 }
4659
4660 // sanity check
4661 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
4662
4663
4664 // Create load nodes to retrieve arguments from the stack
4665 SDValue ArgValue;
4666 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
4667 if (CapArgReg == -1U)
4668 CapArgReg = MF.addLiveIn(Mips::C13, getRegClassFor(CapType));
4669 SDValue Addr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL,
4670 CapArgReg, CapType), VA.getLocMemOffset());
4671 ArgValue = DAG.getLoad(LocVT, DL, Chain, Addr, MachinePointerInfo());
4672 } else {
4673 // The stack pointer offset is relative to the caller stack frame.
4674 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(LocVT.getSizeInBits() / 8,
4675 VA.getLocMemOffset(), true);
4676 SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
4677 ABI.StackAddrSpace()));
4678 ArgValue = DAG.getLoad(
4679 LocVT, DL, Chain, FIN,
4680 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI));
4681 }
4682 OutChains.push_back(ArgValue.getValue(1));
4683
4684 ArgValue = UnpackFromArgumentSlot(ArgValue, VA, Ins[i].ArgVT, DL, DAG);
4685
4686 InVals.push_back(ArgValue);
4687 }
4688 }
4689
4690 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4691 // The mips ABIs for returning structs by value requires that we copy
4692 // the sret argument into $v0 for the return. Save the argument into
4693 // a virtual register so that we can access it from the return points.
4694 if (Ins[i].Flags.isSRet()) {
4695 unsigned Reg = MipsFI->getSRetReturnReg();
4696 if (!Reg) {
4697 Reg = MF.getRegInfo().createVirtualRegister(
4698 getRegClassFor(ABI.IsCheriPureCap() ? CapType :
4699 (ABI.IsN64() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32)));
4700 MipsFI->setSRetReturnReg(Reg);
4701 }
4702 SDValue Copy = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Reg, InVals[i]);
4703 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Copy, Chain);
4704 break;
4705 }
4706 }
4707
4708 if (IsVarArg)
4709 writeVarArgRegs(OutChains, Chain, DL, DAG, CCInfo);
4710
4711 // All stores are grouped in one node to allow the matching between
4712 // the size of Ins and InVals. This only happens when on varg functions
4713 if (!OutChains.empty()) {
4714 OutChains.push_back(Chain);
4715 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, OutChains);
4716 }
4717
4718 return Chain;
4719}

4754
4755SDValue
4756MipsTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
4757 bool IsVarArg,
4758 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
4759 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
4760 const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4761 // CCValAssign - represent the assignment of
4762 // the return value to a location
4763 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
4764 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4765
4766 // CCState - Info about the registers and stack slot.
4767 MipsCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, *DAG.getContext());
4768
4769 // Analyze return values.
4770 CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_Mips);
4771
4772 SDValue Flag;
4773 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
4774 bool zeroV0 = true;
4775 bool zeroV1 = true;
4776 bool zeroC3 = true;
4777
4778 // Copy the result values into the output registers.
4779 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
4780 SDValue Val = OutVals[i];
4781 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
4782 assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
4783 bool UseUpperBits = false;
4784
4785 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
4786 default:
4787 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
4788 case CCValAssign::Full:
4789 break;
4790 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
4791 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
4792 break;
4793 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper:
4794 UseUpperBits = true;
4795 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4796 case CCValAssign::AExt:
4797 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
4798 break;
4799 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper:
4800 UseUpperBits = true;
4801 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4802 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
4803 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
4804 break;
4805 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper:
4806 UseUpperBits = true;
4807 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4808 case CCValAssign::SExt:
4809 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
4810 break;
4811 }
4812
4813 if (UseUpperBits) {
4814 unsigned ValSizeInBits = Outs[i].ArgVT.getSizeInBits();
4815 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits();
4816 Val = DAG.getNode(
4817 ISD::SHL, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val,
4818 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT()));
4819 }
4820
4821 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Val, Flag);
4822 switch (VA.getLocReg()) {
4823 case Mips::V0_64:
4824 case Mips::V0:
4825 zeroV0 = false;
4826 break;
4827 case Mips::V1_64:
4828 case Mips::V1:
4829 zeroV1 = false;
4830 break;
4831 case Mips::C3:
4832 zeroC3 = false;
4833 break;
4834 }
4835
4836 // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together with flags.
4837 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4838 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
4839 }
4840 if (CallConv == CallingConv::CHERI_CCall ||
4841 CallConv == CallingConv::CHERI_CCallee) {
4842 if (zeroV0) {
4843 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Mips::V0_64,
4844 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), Flag);
4845 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4846 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Mips::V0_64, MVT::i64));
4847 }
4848 if (zeroV1) {
4849 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Mips::V1_64,
4850 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), Flag);
4851 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4852 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Mips::V1_64, MVT::i64));
4853 }
4854 if (zeroC3) {
4855 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Mips::C3,
4856 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, CapType), Flag);
4857 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4858 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Mips::C3, CapType));
4859 }
4860 }
4861
4862 // The mips ABIs for returning structs by value requires that we copy
4863 // the sret argument into $v0 for the return. We saved the argument into
4864 // a virtual register in the entry block, so now we copy the value out
4865 // and into $v0.
4866 if (MF.getFunction().hasStructRetAttr()) {
4867 EVT SRetTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), ABI.StackAddrSpace());
4868 unsigned V0 = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::V0_64 : Mips::V0;
4869 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
4870 V0 = Mips::C3;
4871 SRetTy = CapType;
4872 }
4873 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
4874 unsigned Reg = MipsFI->getSRetReturnReg();
4875
4876 if (!Reg)
4877 llvm_unreachable("sret virtual register not created in the entry block");
4878 SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, SRetTy);
4879
4880 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, V0, Val, Flag);
4881 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4882 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(V0, SRetTy));
4883 }
4884
4885 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
4886 // If this function used $c13 we want to zero it before returning so that
4887 // all functions without on-stack arguments can assume that $c13 is null
4888 // on entry
4889 if (MF.getRegInfo().isLiveIn(Mips::C13) || IsVarArg) {
4890 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Lowering return for function with $c13 live-in: "
4891 << MF.getName() << "(is varargs: "
4892 << MF.getFunction().isVarArg() << ")\n");
4893 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Mips::C13,
4894 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, CapType), Flag);
4895 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
4896 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Mips::C13, CapType));
4897 }
4898 }
4899
4900 RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
4901
4902 // Add the flag if we have it.
4903 if (Flag.getNode())
4904 RetOps.push_back(Flag);
4905
4906 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap())
4907 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CapRet, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
4908
4909 // ISRs must use "eret".
4910 if (DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().hasFnAttribute("interrupt"))
4911 return LowerInterruptReturn(RetOps, DL, DAG);
4912
4913 // Standard return on Mips is a "jr $ra"
4914 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ret, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
4915}

4921/// getConstraintType - Given a constraint letter, return the type of
4922/// constraint it is for this target.
4923MipsTargetLowering::ConstraintType
4924MipsTargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
4925 // Mips specific constraints
4926 // GCC config/mips/constraints.md
4927 //
4928 // 'd' : An address register. Equivalent to r
4929 // unless generating MIPS16 code.
4930 // 'y' : Equivalent to r; retained for
4931 // backwards compatibility.
4932 // 'c' : A register suitable for use in an indirect
4933 // jump. This will always be $25 for -mabicalls.
4934 // 'l' : The lo register. 1 word storage.
4935 // 'x' : The hilo register pair. Double word storage.
4936 if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
4937 switch (Constraint[0]) {
4938 default : break;
4939 case 'd':
4940 case 'y':
4941 case 'f':
4942 case 'c':
4943 case 'l':
4944 case 'x':
4945 case 'C':
4946 return C_RegisterClass;
4947 case 'R':
4948 return C_Memory;
4949 }
4950 }
4951
4952 if (Constraint == "ZC")
4953 return C_Memory;
4954
4955 return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint);
4956}
4957
4958/// Examine constraint type and operand type and determine a weight value.
4959/// This object must already have been set up with the operand type
4960/// and the current alternative constraint selected.
4961TargetLowering::ConstraintWeight
4962MipsTargetLowering::getSingleConstraintMatchWeight(
4963 AsmOperandInfo &info, const char *constraint) const {
4964 ConstraintWeight weight = CW_Invalid;
4965 Value *CallOperandVal = info.CallOperandVal;
4966 // If we don't have a value, we can't do a match,
4967 // but allow it at the lowest weight.
4968 if (!CallOperandVal)
4969 return CW_Default;
4970 Type *type = CallOperandVal->getType();
4971 // Look at the constraint type.
4972 switch (*constraint) {
4973 default:
4974 weight = TargetLowering::getSingleConstraintMatchWeight(info, constraint);
4975 break;
4976 case 'd':
4977 case 'y':
4978 if (type->isIntegerTy())
4979 weight = CW_Register;
4980 break;
4981 case 'f': // FPU or MSA register
4982 if (Subtarget.hasMSA() && type->isVectorTy() &&
4983 cast<VectorType>(type)->getBitWidth() == 128)
4984 weight = CW_Register;
4985 else if (type->isFloatTy())
4986 weight = CW_Register;
4987 break;
4988 case 'c': // $25 for indirect jumps
4989 case 'l': // lo register
4990 case 'x': // hilo register pair
4991 if (type->isIntegerTy())
4992 weight = CW_SpecificReg;
4993 break;
4994 case 'I': // signed 16 bit immediate
4995 case 'J': // integer zero
4996 case 'K': // unsigned 16 bit immediate
4997 case 'L': // signed 32 bit immediate where lower 16 bits are 0
4998 case 'N': // immediate in the range of -65535 to -1 (inclusive)
4999 case 'O': // signed 15 bit immediate (+- 16383)
5000 case 'P': // immediate in the range of 65535 to 1 (inclusive)
5001 if (isa<ConstantInt>(CallOperandVal))
5002 weight = CW_Constant;
5003 break;
5004 case 'R':
5005 weight = CW_Memory;
5006 break;
5007 }
5008 return weight;
5009}

5011/// This is a helper function to parse a physical register string and split it
5012/// into non-numeric and numeric parts (Prefix and Reg). The first boolean flag
5013/// that is returned indicates whether parsing was successful. The second flag
5014/// is true if the numeric part exists.
5015static std::pair<bool, bool> parsePhysicalReg(StringRef C, StringRef &Prefix,
5016 unsigned long long &Reg) {
5017 if (C.empty() || C.front() != '{' || C.back() != '}')
5018 return std::make_pair(false, false);
5019
5020 // Search for the first numeric character.
5021 StringRef::const_iterator I, B = C.begin() + 1, E = C.end() - 1;
5022 I = std::find_if(B, E, isdigit);
5023
5024 Prefix = StringRef(B, I - B);
5025
5026 // The second flag is set to false if no numeric characters were found.
5027 if (I == E)
5028 return std::make_pair(true, false);
5029
5030 // Parse the numeric characters.
5031 return std::make_pair(!getAsUnsignedInteger(StringRef(I, E - I), 10, Reg),
5032 true);
5033}
5034
5035EVT MipsTargetLowering::getTypeForExtReturn(LLVMContext &Context, EVT VT,
5036 ISD::NodeType) const {
5037 bool Cond = !Subtarget.isABI_O32() && VT.getSizeInBits() == 32;
5038 EVT MinVT = getRegisterType(Context, Cond ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32);
5039 return VT.bitsLT(MinVT) ? MinVT : VT;
5040}
5041
5042std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> MipsTargetLowering::
5043parseRegForInlineAsmConstraint(StringRef C, MVT VT) const {
5044 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI =
5045 Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
5046 const TargetRegisterClass *RC;
5047 StringRef Prefix;
5048 unsigned long long Reg;
5049
5050 std::pair<bool, bool> R = parsePhysicalReg(C, Prefix, Reg);
5051
5052 if (!R.first)
5053 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5054
5055 if ((Prefix == "hi" || Prefix == "lo")) { // Parse hi/lo.
5056 // No numeric characters follow "hi" or "lo".
5057 if (R.second)
5058 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5059
5060 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Prefix == "hi" ?
5061 Mips::HI32RegClassID : Mips::LO32RegClassID);
5062 return std::make_pair(*(RC->begin()), RC);
5063 } else if (Prefix.startswith("$msa")) {
5064 // Parse $msa(ir|csr|access|save|modify|request|map|unmap)
5065
5066 // No numeric characters follow the name.
5067 if (R.second)
5068 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5069
5070 Reg = StringSwitch<unsigned long long>(Prefix)
5071 .Case("$msair", Mips::MSAIR)
5072 .Case("$msacsr", Mips::MSACSR)
5073 .Case("$msaaccess", Mips::MSAAccess)
5074 .Case("$msasave", Mips::MSASave)
5075 .Case("$msamodify", Mips::MSAModify)
5076 .Case("$msarequest", Mips::MSARequest)
5077 .Case("$msamap", Mips::MSAMap)
5078 .Case("$msaunmap", Mips::MSAUnmap)
5079 .Default(0);
5080
5081 if (!Reg)
5082 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5083
5084 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Mips::MSACtrlRegClassID);
5085 return std::make_pair(Reg, RC);
5086 }
5087
5088 if (!R.second)
5089 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5090
5091 if (Prefix == "$f") { // Parse $f0-$f31.
5092 // If the size of FP registers is 64-bit or Reg is an even number, select
5093 // the 64-bit register class. Otherwise, select the 32-bit register class.
5094 if (VT == MVT::Other)
5095 VT = (Subtarget.isFP64bit() || !(Reg % 2)) ? MVT::f64 : MVT::f32;
5096
5097 RC = getRegClassFor(VT);
5098
5099 if (RC == &Mips::AFGR64RegClass) {
5100 assert(Reg % 2 == 0);
5101 Reg >>= 1;
5102 }
5103 } else if (Prefix == "$fcc") // Parse $fcc0-$fcc7.
5104 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Mips::FCCRegClassID);
5105 else if (Prefix == "$w") { // Parse $w0-$w31.
5106 RC = getRegClassFor((VT == MVT::Other) ? MVT::v16i8 : VT);
5107 } else if (Prefix == "$c") { // Parse $c0-$c31.
5108 assert(Reg != 0 && "$c0 should not end up as an inline asm constraint");
5109 Reg--; // C0 does not exist so we need to subtract one here
5110 RC = getRegClassFor(CapType);
5111 } else { // Parse $0-$31.
5112 assert(Prefix == "$");
5113 RC = getRegClassFor((VT == MVT::Other) ? MVT::i32 : VT);
5114 }
5115
5116 assert(Reg < RC->getNumRegs());
5117 return std::make_pair(*(RC->begin() + Reg), RC);
5118}
5119
5120/// Given a register class constraint, like 'r', if this corresponds directly
5121/// to an LLVM register class, return a register of 0 and the register class
5122/// pointer.
5123std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
5124MipsTargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
5125 StringRef Constraint,
5126 MVT VT) const {
5127 if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
5128 switch (Constraint[0]) {
5129 case 'd': // Address register. Same as 'r' unless generating MIPS16 code.
5130 case 'y': // Same as 'r'. Exists for compatibility.
5131 case 'r':
5132 if (VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i8) {
5133 if (Subtarget.inMips16Mode())
5134 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::CPU16RegsRegClass);
5135 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR32RegClass);
5136 }
5137 if (VT == MVT::i64 && !Subtarget.isGP64bit())
5138 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR32RegClass);
5139 if (VT == MVT::i64 && Subtarget.isGP64bit())
5140 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR64RegClass);
5141 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH; // also allow capability with r (for compatibility)
5142 case 'C':
5143 if (VT == CapType)
5144 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::CheriGPRRegClass);
5145 // This will generate an error message
5146 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5147 case 'f': // FPU or MSA register
5148 if (VT == MVT::v16i8)
5149 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128BRegClass);
5150 else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16)
5151 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128HRegClass);
5152 else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32)
5153 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
5154 else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64)
5155 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128DRegClass);
5156 else if (VT == MVT::f32)
5157 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::FGR32RegClass);
5158 else if ((VT == MVT::f64) && (!Subtarget.isSingleFloat())) {
5159 if (Subtarget.isFP64bit())
5160 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::FGR64RegClass);
5161 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::AFGR64RegClass);
5162 }
5163 break;
5164 case 'c': // register suitable for indirect jump
5165 if (VT == MVT::i32)
5166 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::T9, &Mips::GPR32RegClass);
5167 if (VT == MVT::i64)
5168 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::T9_64, &Mips::GPR64RegClass);
5169 // This will generate an error message
5170 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5171 case 'l': // use the `lo` register to store values
5172 // that are no bigger than a word
5173 if (VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i8)
5174 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::LO0, &Mips::LO32RegClass);
5175 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::LO0_64, &Mips::LO64RegClass);
5176 case 'x': // use the concatenated `hi` and `lo` registers
5177 // to store doubleword values
5178 // Fixme: Not triggering the use of both hi and low
5179 // This will generate an error message
5180 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
5181 }
5182 }
5183
5184 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *> R;
5185 R = parseRegForInlineAsmConstraint(Constraint, VT);
5186
5187 if (R.second)
5188 return R;
5189
5190 return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
5191}
5192
5193/// LowerAsmOperandForConstraint - Lower the specified operand into the Ops
5194/// vector. If it is invalid, don't add anything to Ops.
5195void MipsTargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(SDValue Op,
5196 std::string &Constraint,
5197 std::vector<SDValue>&Ops,
5198 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5199 SDLoc DL(Op);
5200 SDValue Result;
5201
5202 // Only support length 1 constraints for now.
5203 if (Constraint.length() > 1) return;
5204
5205 char ConstraintLetter = Constraint[0];
5206 switch (ConstraintLetter) {
5207 default: break; // This will fall through to the generic implementation
5208 case 'I': // Signed 16 bit constant
5209 // If this fails, the parent routine will give an error
5210 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5211 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5212 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
5213 if (isInt<16>(Val)) {
5214 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5215 break;
5216 }
5217 }
5218 return;
5219 case 'J': // integer zero
5220 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5221 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5222 int64_t Val = C->getZExtValue();
5223 if (Val == 0) {
5224 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Type);
5225 break;
5226 }
5227 }
5228 return;
5229 case 'K': // unsigned 16 bit immediate
5230 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5231 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5232 uint64_t Val = (uint64_t)C->getZExtValue();
5233 if (isUInt<16>(Val)) {
5234 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5235 break;
5236 }
5237 }
5238 return;
5239 case 'L': // signed 32 bit immediate where lower 16 bits are 0
5240 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5241 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5242 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
5243 if ((isInt<32>(Val)) && ((Val & 0xffff) == 0)){
5244 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5245 break;
5246 }
5247 }
5248 return;
5249 case 'N': // immediate in the range of -65535 to -1 (inclusive)
5250 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5251 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5252 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
5253 if ((Val >= -65535) && (Val <= -1)) {
5254 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5255 break;
5256 }
5257 }
5258 return;
5259 case 'O': // signed 15 bit immediate
5260 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5261 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5262 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
5263 if ((isInt<15>(Val))) {
5264 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5265 break;
5266 }
5267 }
5268 return;
5269 case 'P': // immediate in the range of 1 to 65535 (inclusive)
5270 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
5271 EVT Type = Op.getValueType();
5272 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue();
5273 if ((Val <= 65535) && (Val >= 1)) {
5274 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type);
5275 break;
5276 }
5277 }
5278 return;
5279 }
5280
5281 if (Result.getNode()) {
5282 Ops.push_back(Result);
5283 return;
5284 }
5285
5286 TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG);
5287}

5289bool MipsTargetLowering::isLegalAddressingMode(const DataLayout &DL,
5290 const AddrMode &AM, Type *Ty,
5291 unsigned AS, Instruction *I) const {
5292 // No global is ever allowed as a base.
5293 if (AM.BaseGV)
5294 return false;
5295
5296 if (isCheriPointer(AS, &DL)) {
5297 switch (AM.Scale) {
5298 case 0: // "r+i" or just "i", depending on HasBaseReg.
5299 case 1:
5300 return true;
5301 default:
5302 return false;
5303 }
5304 }
5305
5306 switch (AM.Scale) {
5307 case 0: // "r+i" or just "i", depending on HasBaseReg.
5308 break;
5309 case 1:
5310 if (!AM.HasBaseReg) // allow "r+i".
5311 break;
5312 return false; // disallow "r+r" or "r+r+i".
5313 default:
5314 return false;
5315 }
5316
5317 return true;
5318}

5325
5326EVT MipsTargetLowering::getOptimalMemOpType(
5327 uint64_t Size, unsigned DstAlign, unsigned SrcAlign, bool IsMemset,
5328 bool ZeroMemset, bool MemcpyStrSrc,
5329 const AttributeList &FuncAttributes) const {
5330 // If the source alignment is 32 then we are copying something that may
5331 // contain capabilities. If the destination alignment is 32, then we are
5332 // copying to something that may contain capabilities. If both of these is
5333 // true, then we must use capability copies to do preserve tag bits.
5334 // Otherwise, we do copying that will clear the capability tags. For memset,
5335 // the source align will be 0. We don't want to use capabilities in this
5336 // case, because the capability tag will always be 0. For very long memsets,
5337 // we can use the capability registers in the library implementation.
5338 if (Subtarget.isCheri() && (!IsMemset || ZeroMemset)) {
5339 unsigned MinSrcAlign = SrcAlign == 0 ? DstAlign : SrcAlign;
5340 unsigned MinDstAlign = DstAlign == 0 ? SrcAlign : DstAlign;
5341 unsigned Align = IsMemset ? DstAlign : std::min(MinSrcAlign, MinDstAlign);
5342 unsigned CapSize = Subtarget.getCapSizeInBytes();
5343 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << __func__ << " Size=" << Size << " DstAlign=" << DstAlign << " SrcAlign=" << SrcAlign << "\n");
5344 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << __func__ << " CapSize=" << CapSize << " Align=" << Align << "\n");
5345 if (ZeroMemset && (Align >= CapSize) && (Size >= CapSize)) {
5346 // for bzero() always use capability stores of $cnull.
5347 return CapType;
5348 }
5349 // If this is going to include a capability, then pretend that we have to
5350 // copy it using single bytes, which will cause SelectionDAG to decide to
5351 // do the memcpy call.
5352 if (!IsMemset && (Size >= CapSize) && (Align < CapSize) && Align != 0) {
5353 // llvm_unreachable("This function should not be called for underaligned "
5354 // "memcpy greater than CAP_SIZE");
5355 // return MVT::i8; // INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE
5356 return MVT::isVoid; // This will tell selectiondag that a call must be made
5357 }
5358 switch (Align) {
5359 default:
5360 assert(isPowerOf2_32(Align));
5361 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5362 case 0: // Zero means any alignment is fine
5363 if (Size >= CapSize)
5364 return CapType;
5365 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5366 case 16:
5367 if (Size >= CapSize && Subtarget.isCheri128())
5368 return CapType;
5369 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5370 case 8:
5371 if (Size >= CapSize && Subtarget.isCheri64())
5372 return CapType;
5373 return MVT::i64;
5374 case 4: return MVT::i32;
5375 case 2: return MVT::i16;
5376 case 1: return MVT::i8;
5377 }
5378 }
5379
5380 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit())
5381 return MVT::i64;
5382
5383 return MVT::i32;
5384}

5388 if (VT != MVT::f32 && VT != MVT::f64)

5411
5412void MipsTargetLowering::copyByValRegs(
5413 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL, std::vector<SDValue> &OutChains,
5414 SelectionDAG &DAG, const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags,
5415 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals, const Argument *FuncArg,
5416 unsigned FirstReg, unsigned LastReg, const CCValAssign &VA,
5417 MipsCCState &State) const {
5418 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5419 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
5420 unsigned GPRSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes();
5421 unsigned NumRegs = LastReg - FirstReg;
5422 unsigned RegAreaSize = NumRegs * GPRSizeInBytes;
5423 unsigned FrameObjSize = std::max(Flags.getByValSize(), RegAreaSize);
5424 int FrameObjOffset;
5425 ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ByValArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs();
5426
5427 if (RegAreaSize)
5428 FrameObjOffset =
5429 (int)ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(State.getCallingConv()) -
5430 (int)((ByValArgRegs.size() - FirstReg) * GPRSizeInBytes);
5431 else
5432 FrameObjOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset();
5433
5434 // Create frame object.
5435 EVT PtrTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), ABI.StackAddrSpace());
5436 // Make the fixed object stored to mutable so that the load instructions
5437 // referencing it have their memory dependencies added.
5438 // Set the frame object as isAliased which clears the underlying objects
5439 // vector in ScheduleDAGInstrs::buildSchedGraph() resulting in addition of all
5440 // stores as dependencies for loads referencing this fixed object.
5441 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(FrameObjSize, FrameObjOffset, false, true);
5442 SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrTy);
5443 InVals.push_back(FIN);
5444
5445 if (!NumRegs)
5446 return;
5447
5448 // Copy arg registers.
5449 MVT RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(GPRSizeInBytes * 8);
5450 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegTy);
5451
5452 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumRegs; ++I) {
5453 unsigned ArgReg = ByValArgRegs[FirstReg + I];
5454 unsigned VReg = addLiveIn(MF, ArgReg, RC);
5455 unsigned Offset = I * GPRSizeInBytes;
5456 SDValue StorePtr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, FIN, Offset);
5457 SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, DAG.getRegister(VReg, RegTy),
5458 StorePtr, MachinePointerInfo(FuncArg, Offset));
5459 OutChains.push_back(Store);
5460 }
5461}
5462
5463// Copy byVal arg to registers and stack.
5464void MipsTargetLowering::passByValArg(
5465 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL,
5466 std::deque<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>> &RegsToPass,
5467 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &MemOpChains, SDValue StackPtr,
5468 MachineFrameInfo &MFI, SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Arg, unsigned FirstReg,
5469 unsigned LastReg, const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags, bool isLittle,
5470 const CCValAssign &VA) const {
5471 unsigned ByValSizeInBytes = Flags.getByValSize();
5472 unsigned OffsetInBytes = 0; // From beginning of struct
5473 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes();
5474 unsigned Alignment = std::min(Flags.getByValAlign(), RegSizeInBytes);
5475 EVT PtrTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), ABI.StackAddrSpace()),
5476 RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(RegSizeInBytes * 8);
5477 unsigned NumRegs = LastReg - FirstReg;
5478
5479 // Don't pass parts of the struct in integer registers (will break caps)
5480 // TODO: should also not happen in hybrid abi for structs with caps
5481 if (NumRegs && !ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
5482 ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs();
5483 bool LeftoverBytes = (NumRegs * RegSizeInBytes > ByValSizeInBytes);
5484 unsigned I = 0;
5485
5486 // Copy words to registers.
5487 for (; I < NumRegs - LeftoverBytes; ++I, OffsetInBytes += RegSizeInBytes) {
5488 SDValue LoadPtr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Arg, OffsetInBytes);
5489 SDValue LoadVal = DAG.getLoad(RegTy, DL, Chain, LoadPtr,
5490 MachinePointerInfo(), Alignment);
5491 MemOpChains.push_back(LoadVal.getValue(1));
5492 unsigned ArgReg = ArgRegs[FirstReg + I];
5493 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(ArgReg, LoadVal));
5494 }
5495
5496 // Return if the struct has been fully copied.
5497 if (ByValSizeInBytes == OffsetInBytes)
5498 return;
5499
5500 // Copy the remainder of the byval argument with sub-word loads and shifts.
5501 if (LeftoverBytes) {
5502 SDValue Val;
5503
5504 for (unsigned LoadSizeInBytes = RegSizeInBytes / 2, TotalBytesLoaded = 0;
5505 OffsetInBytes < ByValSizeInBytes; LoadSizeInBytes /= 2) {
5506 unsigned RemainingSizeInBytes = ByValSizeInBytes - OffsetInBytes;
5507
5508 if (RemainingSizeInBytes < LoadSizeInBytes)
5509 continue;
5510
5511 // Load subword.
5512 SDValue LoadPtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, Arg,
5513 DAG.getConstant(OffsetInBytes, DL,
5514 PtrTy));
5515 SDValue LoadVal = DAG.getExtLoad(
5516 ISD::ZEXTLOAD, DL, RegTy, Chain, LoadPtr, MachinePointerInfo(),
5517 MVT::getIntegerVT(LoadSizeInBytes * 8), Alignment);
5518 MemOpChains.push_back(LoadVal.getValue(1));
5519
5520 // Shift the loaded value.
5521 unsigned Shamt;
5522
5523 if (isLittle)
5524 Shamt = TotalBytesLoaded * 8;
5525 else
5526 Shamt = (RegSizeInBytes - (TotalBytesLoaded + LoadSizeInBytes)) * 8;
5527
5528 SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, RegTy, LoadVal,
5529 DAG.getConstant(Shamt, DL, MVT::i32));
5530
5531 if (Val.getNode())
5532 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, RegTy, Val, Shift);
5533 else
5534 Val = Shift;
5535
5536 OffsetInBytes += LoadSizeInBytes;
5537 TotalBytesLoaded += LoadSizeInBytes;
5538 Alignment = std::min(Alignment, LoadSizeInBytes);
5539 }
5540
5541 unsigned ArgReg = ArgRegs[FirstReg + I];
5542 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(ArgReg, Val));
5543 return;
5544 }
5545 }
5546
5547 // Copy remainder of byval arg to it with memcpy.
5548 unsigned MemCpySize = ByValSizeInBytes - OffsetInBytes;
5549 SDValue Src = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Arg, OffsetInBytes);
5550 SDValue Dst = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, StackPtr, VA.getLocMemOffset());
5551 Chain = DAG.getMemcpy(
5552 Chain, DL, Dst, Src, DAG.getConstant(MemCpySize, DL, PtrTy), Alignment,
5553 /*isVolatile=*/false, /*AlwaysInline=*/false,
5554 /*isTailCall=*/false, /*MustPreserveCheriCapabilities=*/false,
5555 MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
5556 MemOpChains.push_back(Chain);
5557}
5558
5559void MipsTargetLowering::writeVarArgRegs(std::vector<SDValue> &OutChains,
5560 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL,
5561 SelectionDAG &DAG,
5562 CCState &State) const {
5563 ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ArgRegs = ABI.GetVarArgRegs();
5564 unsigned Idx = State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs);
5565 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes();
5566 MVT RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(RegSizeInBytes * 8);
5567 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegTy);
5568 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5569 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
5570 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo<MipsFunctionInfo>();
5571
5572 // Offset of the first variable argument from stack pointer.
5573 int VaArgOffset;
5574
5575 if (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()) {
5576 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(RegSizeInBytes, 0, true);
5577 MipsFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI);
5578 return;
5579 }
5580
5581 if (ArgRegs.size() == Idx)
5582 VaArgOffset = alignTo(State.getNextStackOffset(), RegSizeInBytes);
5583 else {
5584 VaArgOffset =
5585 (int)ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(State.getCallingConv()) -
5586 (int)(RegSizeInBytes * (ArgRegs.size() - Idx));
5587 }
5588
5589 // Record the frame index of the first variable argument
5590 // which is a value necessary to VASTART.
5591 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(RegSizeInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
5592 MipsFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI);
5593
5594 // Copy the integer registers that have not been used for argument passing
5595 // to the argument register save area. For O32, the save area is allocated
5596 // in the caller's stack frame, while for N32/64, it is allocated in the
5597 // callee's stack frame.
5598 for (unsigned I = Idx; I < ArgRegs.size();
5599 ++I, VaArgOffset += RegSizeInBytes) {
5600 unsigned Reg = addLiveIn(MF, ArgRegs[I], RC);
5601 SDValue ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, RegTy);
5602 FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(RegSizeInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
5603 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
5604 ABI.StackAddrSpace()));
5605 SDValue Store =
5606 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo());
5607 cast<StoreSDNode>(Store.getNode())->getMemOperand()->setValue(
5608 (Value *)nullptr);
5609 OutChains.push_back(Store);
5610 }
5611}
5612
5613void MipsTargetLowering::HandleByVal(CCState *State, unsigned &Size,
5614 unsigned Align) const {
5615 const TargetFrameLowering *TFL = Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
5616
5617 assert(Size && "Byval argument's size shouldn't be 0.");
5618
5619 Align = std::min(Align, TFL->getStackAlignment());
5620
5621 unsigned FirstReg = 0;
5622 unsigned NumRegs = 0;
5623
5624 if (State->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::Fast) {
5625 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes();
5626 ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> IntArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs();
5627 // FIXME: The O32 case actually describes no shadow registers.
5628 const MCPhysReg *ShadowRegs =
5629 ABI.IsO32() ? IntArgRegs.data() : Mips64DPRegs;
5630
5631 // We used to check the size as well but we can't do that anymore since
5632 // CCState::HandleByVal() rounds up the size after calling this function.
5633 assert(!(Align % RegSizeInBytes) &&
5634 "Byval argument's alignment should be a multiple of"
5635 "RegSizeInBytes.");
5636
5637 FirstReg = State->getFirstUnallocated(IntArgRegs);
5638
5639 // If Align > RegSizeInBytes, the first arg register must be even.
5640 // FIXME: This condition happens to do the right thing but it's not the
5641 // right way to test it. We want to check that the stack frame offset
5642 // of the register is aligned.
5643 if ((Align > RegSizeInBytes) && (FirstReg % 2)) {
5644 State->AllocateReg(IntArgRegs[FirstReg], ShadowRegs[FirstReg]);
5645 ++FirstReg;
5646 }
5647
5648 // Mark the registers allocated.
5649 Size = alignTo(Size, RegSizeInBytes);
5650 for (unsigned I = FirstReg; Size > 0 && (I < IntArgRegs.size());
5651 Size -= RegSizeInBytes, ++I, ++NumRegs)
5652 State->AllocateReg(IntArgRegs[I], ShadowRegs[I]);
5653 }
5654
5655 State->addInRegsParamInfo(FirstReg, FirstReg + NumRegs);
5656}
5657
5658MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitPseudoSELECT(MachineInstr &MI,
5659 MachineBasicBlock *BB,
5660 bool isFPCmp,
5661 unsigned Opc) const {
5662 assert(!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32()) &&
5663 "Subtarget already supports SELECT nodes with the use of"
5664 "conditional-move instructions.");
5665
5666 const TargetInstrInfo *TII =
5667 Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
5668 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
5669
5670 // To "insert" a SELECT instruction, we actually have to insert the
5671 // diamond control-flow pattern. The incoming instruction knows the
5672 // destination vreg to set, the condition code register to branch on, the
5673 // true/false values to select between, and a branch opcode to use.
5674 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
5675 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
5676
5677 // thisMBB:
5678 // ...
5679 // TrueVal = ...
5680 // setcc r1, r2, r3
5681 // bNE r1, r0, copy1MBB
5682 // fallthrough --> copy0MBB
5683 MachineBasicBlock *thisMBB = BB;
5684 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
5685 MachineBasicBlock *copy0MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
5686 MachineBasicBlock *sinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
5687 F->insert(It, copy0MBB);
5688 F->insert(It, sinkMBB);
5689
5690 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to sinkMBB.
5691 sinkMBB->splice(sinkMBB->begin(), BB,
5692 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
5693 sinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
5694
5695 // Next, add the true and fallthrough blocks as its successors.
5696 BB->addSuccessor(copy0MBB);
5697 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB);
5698
5699 if (isFPCmp) {
5700 // bc1[tf] cc, sinkMBB
5701 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Opc))
5702 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
5703 .addMBB(sinkMBB);
5704 } else {
5705 // bne rs, $0, sinkMBB
5706 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Opc))
5707 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
5708 .addReg(Mips::ZERO)
5709 .addMBB(sinkMBB);
5710 }
5711
5712 // copy0MBB:
5713 // %FalseValue = ...
5714 // # fallthrough to sinkMBB
5715 BB = copy0MBB;
5716
5717 // Update machine-CFG edges
5718 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB);
5719
5720 // sinkMBB:
5721 // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, thisMBB ], [ %FalseValue, copy0MBB ]
5722 // ...
5723 BB = sinkMBB;
5724
5725 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(0).getReg())
5726 .addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg())
5727 .addMBB(thisMBB)
5728 .addReg(MI.getOperand(3).getReg())
5729 .addMBB(copy0MBB);
5730
5731 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
5732
5733 return BB;
5734}
5735
5736MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitPseudoD_SELECT(MachineInstr &MI,
5737 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
5738 assert(!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32()) &&
5739 "Subtarget already supports SELECT nodes with the use of"
5740 "conditional-move instructions.");
5741
5742 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
5743 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
5744
5745 // D_SELECT substitutes two SELECT nodes that goes one after another and
5746 // have the same condition operand. On machines which don't have
5747 // conditional-move instruction, it reduces unnecessary branch instructions
5748 // which are result of using two diamond patterns that are result of two
5749 // SELECT pseudo instructions.
5750 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
5751 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
5752
5753 // thisMBB:
5754 // ...
5755 // TrueVal = ...
5756 // setcc r1, r2, r3
5757 // bNE r1, r0, copy1MBB
5758 // fallthrough --> copy0MBB
5759 MachineBasicBlock *thisMBB = BB;
5760 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
5761 MachineBasicBlock *copy0MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
5762 MachineBasicBlock *sinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
5763 F->insert(It, copy0MBB);
5764 F->insert(It, sinkMBB);
5765
5766 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to sinkMBB.
5767 sinkMBB->splice(sinkMBB->begin(), BB,
5768 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
5769 sinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
5770
5771 // Next, add the true and fallthrough blocks as its successors.
5772 BB->addSuccessor(copy0MBB);
5773 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB);
5774
5775 // bne rs, $0, sinkMBB
5776 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BNE))
5777 .addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg())
5778 .addReg(Mips::ZERO)
5779 .addMBB(sinkMBB);
5780
5781 // copy0MBB:
5782 // %FalseValue = ...
5783 // # fallthrough to sinkMBB
5784 BB = copy0MBB;
5785
5786 // Update machine-CFG edges
5787 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB);
5788
5789 // sinkMBB:
5790 // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, thisMBB ], [ %FalseValue, copy0MBB ]
5791 // ...
5792 BB = sinkMBB;
5793
5794 // Use two PHI nodes to select two reults
5795 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(0).getReg())
5796 .addReg(MI.getOperand(3).getReg())
5797 .addMBB(thisMBB)
5798 .addReg(MI.getOperand(5).getReg())
5799 .addMBB(copy0MBB);
5800 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
5801 .addReg(MI.getOperand(4).getReg())
5802 .addMBB(thisMBB)
5803 .addReg(MI.getOperand(6).getReg())
5804 .addMBB(copy0MBB);
5805
5806 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
5807
5808 return BB;
5809}

5811// FIXME? Maybe this could be a TableGen attribute on some registers and
5812// this table could be generated automatically from RegInfo.
5813unsigned MipsTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char* RegName, EVT VT,
5814 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5815 // Named registers is expected to be fairly rare. For now, just support $28
5816 // since the linux kernel uses it.
5817 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) {
5818 unsigned Reg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(RegName)
5819 .Case("$28", Mips::GP_64)
5820 .Default(0);
5821 if (Reg)
5822 return Reg;
5823 } else {
5824 unsigned Reg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(RegName)
5825 .Case("$28", Mips::GP)
5826 .Default(0);
5827 if (Reg)
5828 return Reg;
5829 }
5830 report_fatal_error("Invalid register name global variable");
5831}
